title: sunshine refresher
directions: Blend Marshmallow Creme and 1/4 cup orange juice in blender or at medium speed on electric mixer until smooth.
Add remaining juice and eggs; beat until foamy.
Makes eight 1/2 cup servings.

title: refried beans
directions: Heat chicken broth in a 10-inch non-stick skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add chopped onions and cook until soft.
Add pinto beans; cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Mash beans; stir in chili powder, salsa, cumin, salt and pepper.
Add more chicken broth to skillet, if necessary.
Cook and stir until a smooth paste forms, about 5 minutes.
Garnish with grated Cheddar cheese melted on top.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Test in 30 to 40 minutes.

title: nutty chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, beat eggs until well combined. Add Karo, nuts, chocolate chips, sugar, margarine and vanilla. Mix until well blended. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool completely.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix by hand margarine, crumbs, powdered sugar and pecans.
Pour into glass (13 x 9-inch) pan.
Beat cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, eggs and lemon juice.
Pour into crust (glass pan) and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Spread blueberry pie filling on top.
Cover with tinfoil and refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: lasagne
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in three noodles.
Brown meat. Add onion.
Drain off fat.
Add Ragu to meat and onion.
Cover noodles with 1/2 of sauce, then half of Cheddar cheese, half of Mozzarella cheese and half of Parmesan cheese.
Add 3 noodles, rest of sauce, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover 1st half hour.
Uncover last half hour.

title: sticky buns
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread dough in saucepan.
Mix and stir until melted and smooth.
Tear apart 1 loaf of bread dough and put in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour part of the pudding mixture over top of bread dough.
Fill in holes with second loaf of bread dough.
Pour remaining mixture over bread dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: double crispy chicken
directions: Measure crushed corn flake cereal into a shallow dish or pan. Set aside.
In small mixing bowl, beat egg and milk slightly. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth.
Dip chicken in batter; coat with crushed cereal.
Place in single layer, skin side up, in greased or foil lined shallow baking pan. Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Do not cover pan or turn while baking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy; beat in peanut butter and sugar and slowly add milk.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into prepared crust.
Freeze until firm and serve.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the cereal, sugar, flour and salt using a large spoon, then mix in the buttermilk with baking soda, oil and eggs.
Add buttermilk.
After everything is mixed well, do not mix again.
Fill muffin tins half full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Store any leftover dough in an airtight container in fridge.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil and pumpkin; mix. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix.
Add vanilla, flour, raisins and pineapple.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: lollipops
directions: You will need 12 wooden or lollipop sticks.

title: american-style stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, combine chicken with soy sauce, wine and ginger. Let stand 15 to 30 minutes.
Preheat 1 tablespoon oil in wok, uncovered, at medium high, about 2 minutes.
Add carrots; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup chicken broth; cover and steam 4 minutes. Remove carrots.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok.
Add broccoli and celery; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Push up the side.
Add onions and mushrooms; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove all vegetables.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok.
Add 1/2 of the chicken with marinade; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Push up the side.
Repeat with remaining meat.
Return vegetables to wok.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup chicken broth, cornstarch and sugar.
Stir into chicken and vegetable mixture and cook until thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except sour cream together well. Fold in	sour
cream.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: betty's pound cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: knockwurst and noodles
directions: Chop and fry onion in butter.
Mix together all ingredients, except noodles. Cook over low flame until cheese melts.
Add cooked noodles and serve.
Serves 8.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks with water.
Add sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, raisins, honey and vanilla. Spread coconut on flat pan. Drop spoonfuls of mixture on coconut and roll. Chill.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix and press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside crust and preheat oven at 300° so that when filling is complete, oven will be ready for baking.

title: low country boil
directions: Add shrimp seasoning to approximately 2 gallons of water. Heat to boiling point.
Cook sausage, corn and cut up potatoes together until all is tender.
Then add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp is done, approximately 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Put milk and marshmallows in a pan and place on low heat. Stir often until marshmallows are melted.
Crush the vanilla wafers and chop the cherries and nuts.
Then put all the dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Add the milk mixture.
Mix with your hands.
Grease as many pans as you need and press the mixture into the pan.
Place in icebox and the next day it is ready to slice.
This makes a lot of fruit cake.

title: spiced apple squares
directions: Cut butter into dry cake mix; set aside 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling evenly over bottom layer.

title: beef short ribs - barbecue
directions: Have beef ribs be the size of serving pieces.
Season them with the mixture of salt and both peppers.
Place in large skillet and brown in hot oil.
Cover with sliced onions after you have placed the ribs in a large baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the meat.
(Catsup water just means put the 3/4 cup water in the same measuring cup that you used to put in the 3/4 cup catsup.) Cover tightly; bake in a moderate (350°) oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.
Uncover the last 15 minutes to brown.
Serves 6.

title: cherry cheese petite pies
directions: Put one vanilla wafer in each cupcake tin.
Mix all of the remaining ingredients together (except for filling).
Fill each tin 3/4 full of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cooled, top with pie filling.
Yields about 16.

title: hershey's doubly chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.

title: company dessert
directions: Mix Ritz crackers, oleo and nuts.
Press in pan and chill. Reserve a few crumbs for top.
Mix pudding and milk as directed on package.
Just use 2 cups milk.
Partly melt ice cream.
Add to pudding.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix with ice cream mix. Pour over cracker crust in pan.
Put crumbs on top.
Store in refrigerator.
Can use two 8 x 8-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan. Can make 2 days ahead of time.
Serves 15.

title: delicious and easy onion bread
directions: Make up your favorite biscuit dough or use any prepackaged biscuit mix.
Cook a cup of sliced onions in butter until melted, seasoned as you desire.
Spread the onion mixture onto the dough. Roll the biscuit dough flat as you would for a jelly roll, then spread with butter.
Roll up and bake following the instructions for baking biscuits.

title: baked beans
directions: Simmer 1 hour.
Stir often.
Serves 9 or 10 people.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and bell pepper until meat is broken up and almost done.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cover dish with foil while baking.

title: spanish potato omelet
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
In skillet, saute onion and potatoes in olive oil.
Cook on medium heat until potatoes are very well done, stirring often to prevent sticking.
Drain potatoes and reserve olive oil.
Put eggs in a bowl and add drained potatoes. Let sit for 5 minutes.
Cover bottom of skillet with reserved oil. Heat over medium setting.
Add egg mixture.
Carefully test to make sure eggs are cooking uniformly, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Working a spatula around the sides of the skillet, turn omelet onto a large platter.
Push gently back into skillet to cook other side for approximately 1 to 2 minutes.
For a firmer omelet, increase cooking time.

title: grilled marinated pork tenderloins
directions: Place tenderloins in a zip-top heavy-duty plastic bag.
Pour dressing over tenderloins.
Seal and refrigerate 8 hours.
Remove tenderloins from marinade.
Insert meat thermometer into tenderloins, being careful not to touch fat.
Grill tenderloins, covered, over hot coals 12 to 15 minutes or until thermometer registers 160°, turning them once.
Yields 6 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Bring real butter, margarine and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly.
Line a cookie sheet with foil and lay out 1 1/2 packages of graham crackers (separated).
Pour above ingredients over crackers and then a package of semi-sweet morsels.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: easy scallops
directions: Cut scallops with oil and place in a single layer into a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Sprinkle with garlic and dill. Place in 350° oven for approximately 10 minutes or until done. Serve hot.

title: zucchini hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine all ingredients except squash.
Fold in squash.
Use a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares and serve warm

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix well and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: frozen raspberry brownie dessert
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions, using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add meat and cook until done; drain.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Place 1/2 of mixture in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and top with 4 slices of cheese.
Pour rest of meat mixture over cheese and add remaining cheese slices.
Place biscuits over top and bake at 400° about 15 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple and mix as much juice as needed.
Pour in 2 (9-inch) baked pie shells and chill.
Top with Cool Whip and red cherries and serve.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar and leave overnight.
Combine marshmallows and pineapple; leave overnight.
Combine with Cool Whip and freeze.
Use freezer containers and only thaw as needed. Leftover can be refrozen.
Nuts can be added.
I do not because I double the recipe and freeze in boxes.
I don't think nuts freeze as well.

title: carry-out casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper; set aside.
Brown beef; add flour.
Combine beef, vegetables and tomato sauce; simmer for 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and divide into two 9 x 13-inch pans or large casserole dishes. (This freezes well, so one casserole can be saved for a future time.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.
This is an excellent casserole for potlucks and large groups.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil all but cheese until tender.
Add dash of red pepper sauce and cheese.
Heat just until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: vera's nantucket baked beans
directions: Wash beans; soak overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Combine beans with sugar and dry mustard and place in bean pot or loaf pan.
Cut onion into two pieces and push onion and slices of mixed pork down into beans.
Bake several hours at 325°.
Check occasionally.
Add small amounts of water, if necessary.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
In a saucepan combine water, margarine and cocoa.
Heat until it boils. Pour over flour mixture and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add soda and vanilla to buttermilk.
Add to batter.
Pour into 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Do not grease or flour pan.
Ten minutes before cake is done, make the icing.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line a 12 x 15-inch pan with graham crackers broken apart. Boil sugar and margarine for 2 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla. Spoon over crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and place on foil.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and spread over top.
Allow to cool.

title: black russian bundt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix at low speed about 1 minute; beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 60 minutes.
Let cool in pan a few minutes.
Invert on plate or rack.

title: gretchen's pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Gradually add eggs, flour and almond extract.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: joy pie
directions: Mix butter, flour and pecans; mix well.
Spread into cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fola friendship tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls for each cup of boiling water.
Recipe makes 5 cups of dry mix.
Makes a nice gift.
Enjoy!

title: barbecue sauce no. 1
directions: Combine all and bring to a boil, then simmer 15 minutes.

title: meal in a frypan
directions: Brown beef in hot shortening in electric skillet set at 380°. Stir in onions, tomatoes, beans and seasonings.
Cover, reduce heat to 300° and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Serves 6.

title: white pralines
directions: Boil sugar and evaporated milk for 5 minutes after or when it comes to a hard boil.
Add marshmallows.
Mix well.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Remove from fire and beat until it begins to get thick and sugary.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Should make about 24 pieces.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until barely tender; drain.
Cut up slightly; arrange in buttered casserole.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese; spoon over vegetables.
Top with nuts and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: georgia corn pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine corn, eggs, sugar, salt and cornstarch. Mix well. Add milk; blend until ingredients are covered. Cut butter into small pieces and mix in corn batter. Pour into buttered 3-quart baking dish. Place bacon on top. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter, sugar and cream cheese together until creamy.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into shells; refrigerate.

title: fruit salad cake
directions: Mix fruit and egg together, then add flour and other ingredients. Pour into lightly greased pan, top with 1/2 C nuts and 1/2 C brown sugar.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, onion and cheese in a greased baking dish. Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Blend soup and milk. Pour over potatoes. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: ground pork burritos
directions: Saute pork with chopped yellow onion until browned and cooked through.
Add green onions, garlic, soy sauce and sesame oil. Cook on medium-low for 2 minutes, or until onions are tender. Warm tortillas at 300° for a few minutes.
Spread 1 tablespoon hoisin or plum sauce on each tortilla so meat mixture is snugly enclosed.
Garnish with sliced pepper and serve with fried rice, if desired.
Serve immediately, passing extra sauce on the side.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and meat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, kidney beans, chili powder, salt, bay leaf, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, adding liquid or water, if needed.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Cream the butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In a frying pan, a deep dish one if you have it, melt the margarine and add garlic.
Or if you have a nonstick pan, you could try the cooking spray.
Stir-fry the chicken after you cut it into bite-size pieces.
Cook until almost done, then remove from the pan.
Add broccoli.
Add extra margarine if needed. Cover the pan to give the broccoli a chance to cook.
Add the green pepper and onion when broccoli begins to soften.
Add zucchini when peppers are beginning to soften.
Add sun-dried tomatoes now, too.

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil 1 cup water and stick of margarine (or butter).
Add flour, stir and remove from stove.
Beat eggs into mixture (one at a time) thoroughly.
On a greased pan, add tablespoons of the mixture.
It should make approximately 12 to 15 puffs.
Bake at 450° 15 minutes and then reduce to 350° for 40 minutes.
When cooled, slice and fill.
Whip instant pudding, cream and milk until thick enough for filling.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour juice and ginger ale over sherbet.

title: sweet and sour pot roast
directions: Using 6-quart sauce pot, brown meat in shortening; season with salt and pepper.
Add onions, mix water, tomato sauce and garlic; pour over meat.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours; mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat; cover and continue baking for about 2 hours longer, or until meat is tender.
Serve the delicious sauce as gravy.

title: no-fail flaky pie crust
directions: Combine and work with fingers to pea size crumbs.
Place in plastic bag and refrigerate.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: sour cream cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in cranberry sauce and drained pineapple.
Add pecans.
Stir in sour cream and pour into a salad mold.
Chill and serve.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: ice cream torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 2 (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) jelly roll pans with waxed paper.
(If you have only 1 jelly roll pan, bake half batter at one time.)
Prepare cake as directed on package.
Divide batter evenly in pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Immediately invert onto towel.
Peel off paper.
Cool on racks.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, spices, soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar, molasses and shortening.
Stir in flour mixture, then add boiling water, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.
Let cool 1/2 minute before removing from pan.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges with juice in a bowl. Beat 2 minutes.
Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in hollowed out round bread.
Wrap tightly in foil and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Serve with bread pieces.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, sausage and oregano together.
Add cheese and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel potatoes and cook in water until done.
Drain well and mash
with
potato masher.
Add butter while potatoes are hot
or melt
before
adding.
Add
egg
yolks, sugar, syrup, allspice, cinnamon and vanilla; mix well.
Divide between pie shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar to soft ball stage. Add vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow.
Beat.
It takes very little beating. Pour into a well buttered plate.

title: rene's chicken francese
directions: Mix breadcrumbs and flour together (equal parts) with parsley, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in beaten egg and then bread crumb, flour mixture.

title: boyd's strawberry-banana ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except strawberries and
bananas.
Then add fruit and homogenized milk to top of freezer.
Freeze, remove splasher and pack in ice for 30 minutes.

title: microwave caramels
directions: Put the butter, sugar and syrup in a bowl and cook until 265°. Add the cream and vanilla.
Bring to 250°.
Pour into buttered glass pan. Cool. Cut and wrap.
Need microwave candy thermometer.

title: lemon carrot cake supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix mincemeat, carrots and nuts; toss with 1/2 cup flour.
In another bowl, mix oil, sugar and lemon juice.
Add eggs one at a time, beating between additions.
Sift and stir together all dry ingredients; add to egg and sugar mixture.
Mix well. Turn into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cook 15 minutes; turn out of pan.
Eat plain or serve with lemon sauce or glaze as desired.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix corn, sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread all ingredients together, except pecans in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle top of ingredients with pecans. Pour melted butter over all.
The ingredients will mix together as the cake bakes.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: big orange sheet cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix and dry orange Jell-O together. Add water and oil. Beat in eggs. Add vanilla. Beat 5 minutes at medium speed. Pour in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. When done, poke holes in the cake with the end of a wooden spoon and pour glaze.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Flatten chicken breasts and coat with flour.
Brown in hot oil in large frying pan or skillet.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Spoon off fat.
Combine soup, spices and water in pan.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to pan.
Cover, cook 5 more minutes. Removing lid and top each chicken piece with cheese.
Heat until cheese begins to melt.
Serve with noodles.

title: marinated green bean salad
directions: Clean and steam green beans until crisp-tender. Drain and cool. Place beans in a bowl. Add onion and toss with dressing. Refrigerate and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and pull meat off bone.
Make stuffing, using 1 1/2 cups of chicken juice for water.
Mix sour cream, soup, onion, salt and pepper to taste with chicken.
Cook chopped broccoli and drain.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; add soy sauce and oil.
Cool.
In medium size bowl, combine vegetables.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables and toss.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Makes five 1-cup servings.

title: sausage and cabbage pot pie
directions: Cook sausage and onion in Dutch oven, stirring occasionally until sausage is done.
Drain.
Stir in sugar, salt, cabbage and tomatoes.
Break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.

title: banana smoothy beverage
directions: Combine the ingredients in a blender and puree until smooth. Pour into champagne glasses.
Serve with pineapple chunk for garnish.
Makes 2 servings.
One serving = 65 calories, 0 9 protein, 13 g. carbohydrate, 0 gram fat and 11 mg. sodium.

title: frog cookies
directions: Mix egg white and brown sugar.
Add vanilla and pecans. Using hands,
add
more pecans until the mixture is not gooey. Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for
minutes.
Turn off oven and leave cookies in oven for
30 minutes more.
Remove cooled cookies from cookie sheet and store in an airtight container.

title: fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in milk, then flour mixture and brown lightly in shortenings.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and plenty paprika.
Put in baking pan.
Add a
bit
of
water.
Cover and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
In another container mix the remaining 4 ingredients; mix well.
Pour the liquid over the apple mixture, mix well and chill.

title: banana pudding(from scratch)
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Stir in eggs, a little at a time. Cook for 2 minutes more.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour over cookies and bananas.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas, onions and peppers.
Mix salad dressing and sugar; layer on peppers.
Continue with cheese and bacon bits. Better if chilled 1 hour before serving.
Mix ingredients before serving.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in sweetened milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Arrange bananas on bottom of pie shell.
Pour filling over bananas; cover.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; boil juice (you should have 2 cups of juice). Pour over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cheese that has been warmed to room temperature, pimento, pineapple, celery, nuts and a pinch of salt.
Fold in whipped cream and chill.

title: twenty-four hour vegetable salad(serves 12)
directions: In bottom of large straight-edge bowl, place 3 cups of the lettuce; sprinkle with a little sugar, salt and pepper.
Layer sliced eggs atop lettuce in bowl, standing some on edge, if desired.
Sprinkle generously with salt.

title: clam balls
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, clam juice and all. Mix until well blended.
Shape into rounded balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet; sprinkle with powdered butter and bake in 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: speedy tortellini soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil.
Add onion, carrot and garlic. Cook, stirring frequently until onion is translucent, about 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and stir in tortellini.
Simmer until tortellini is cooked 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in spinach, peas, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Peel apples and cut into paper thin slices.
Mix with granulated sugar, nutmeg, salt and lemon juice.
Pack as firmly as possible in a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine flour and brown sugar; add butter and cut in until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over apples; press down firmly, especially at edges to retain juice.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until apples are tender.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sour cream and coconut cake
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, vanilla and 1 package coconut in bowl; mix well.
Chill overnight.
Prepare and bake cake mix using package directions for 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Split cooled layers to make 4 layers.
Spread sour cream mixture between layers and over top and side of cake.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 package coconut.
Chill for 2 days before serving.
Chilling for 2 days makes cake moister.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: strawberry citrus snack block
directions: In a large heatproof bowl, sprinkle gelatin over water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add juice, stirring until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Stir in syrup.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover. Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Cut into blocks with a knife or shapes with cookie cutters.
Serve cold.
Makes about 3 dozen blocks.

title: caramel corn
directions: Baking Temperature: 250°.
Baking Time: 1 hour.

title: karo crazy crunch
directions: Mix popped corn and nuts on a buttered cookie sheet.
Combine sugar, margarine and Karo in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mixture will turn a light caramel color.
Pour over popcorn, nut mixture and mix to coat.
Spread out to dry.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container.

title: cosmopolitan casserole(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spread sauerkraut in bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Top with tomato slices.
Dot with dressing and margarine. Cover with corned beef. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

Remove casserole from oven. Separate biscuits into three layers. Slightly overlap biscuit layers on casserole to form 3 rows. Sprinkle with potato chips and caraway seeds. Bake at 400° for 15 or 20 minutes until biscuit topping is golden brown.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Pour all ingredients in ice cream freezer and start.
When freezer stops, sherbet is ready.

title: mushroom meringues
directions: Briefly beat eggs at moderate slow speed until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Increase speed to moderate and beat another minute until whites hold soft shape.
Continue to beat and add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add vanilla when half the sugar has been added.
Increase speed to high and beat 7 to 8 minutes until meringue is very stiff and the sugar is dissolved.

title: one-two-three-four cake
directions: Melt butter at room temperature and cream with sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating thoroughly after each one is added.
Sift dry ingredients together three times and add alternately with milk and vanilla to creamed mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.
Use Never Fail Chocolate Icing.

title: southern pot roast
directions: Brown beef on all 4 sides. Mix 2 cups water.
Cook in a 350° oven until tender. Serve with brown gravy.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Soak the raisins in the hot water.
Put the remaining ingredients in a bowl and mix them well.
Add raisins and hot water; stir them in.
If you do not want raisins, just add the hot water.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked deep dish pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mary's taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 10-15 min. Top with cheese.

title: beef roll mozzarella
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper, onion, egg and bread crumbs. Drain mushrooms.
Add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Add liquid to meat mixture.
Mix.
Press into a 14 x 10-inch rectangle of wax paper.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella, leaving 1/2-inch boarder.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place seam-side down in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread 1/2 tomato sauce over it.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Mix remaining sauce and mushrooms; spread over roll. Bake 10 more minutes.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Beat together softened margarine, sugar and eggs, then mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour in a greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour or tests done.

title: easy veggie dill dip
directions: Mix and blend well together all ingredients, making sure they are thoroughly mixed.
A wire whip works best.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve with all kinds of fresh vegetables.
Also very good to garnish hamburgers, cheeseburgers and chicken sandwiches.

title: chocolate christmas treats
directions: Melt the butter and chocolate. Add milk and sugar, keep heating and stirring until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat, stir in oats, nuts, and vanilla. Allow to cool to medium warm. Place on wax paper lined cookie sheet.

title: sister grace's sausage biscuits
directions: Crumble breakfast patties.
Add Rediburger; set aside. Prepare Stove Top stuffing following directions on box.
Combine all the ingredients, using seasonings as you desire.
Add a little flour if the consistency is not firm enough to form patties.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream, Monterey Jack cheese, onion, chilies and soup. Set aside 1/3 of this mixture. Spoon remaining mixture into tortillas and roll. Place in large pan. Cover with the 1/3 mixture. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and olives. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Partly thaw hash browns.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together and cook at 350° for 1 hour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: split pea and barley soup
directions: Put all ingredients in 4-quart pot and simmer, uncovered, 1 hour or until all is tender.

title: vidalia onion cheese dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onions in butter.
Blend with mayonnaise, cheese, Tabasco sauce and garlic.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: hash quiche
directions: *Use 2 (15 oz.) cans for a deep dish.

title: deviled guacamole
directions: Mash avocados with fork; stir in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve with corn chips and assorted crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 2-quart dish.
Let potatoes cool slightly.
Stir in all ingredients except cheese. Spread in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes more.
If desired, sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter in Dutch oven for 3 minutes.
Add meat; brown, breaking up as it cooks.
Add seasonings.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce and water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Layer tomato meat mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan with cooked noodles.
Make sure noodles are well covered with sauce.
Top with sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake.
Cut and serve like lasagna.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
May be made night before, refrigerated and baked when needed.

title: fresh sweet potato salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir well. Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Pour dressing over sweet potato mixture.
Stir well. Cover and chill. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: food drop sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking soda; then set aside.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions and pour over coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together over low heat.
Pour in confectioners sugar until well smoothed.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place cut-up chicken in pan.
Saute onions and mushrooms and add to chicken.
Mix together sour cream and soup; spread evenly over chicken mixture.
Crush crackers.
Put over sour cream mixture.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until bubbling.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender; mix until all ingredients are mixed together.
Serve with chips.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion and beef until hot, but not browned. Season. Place 3 cups cabbage in casserole dish and cover with meat. Top with remaining cabbage and pour soup over top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon squares
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together 2 cups flour and 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar.
Cut oleo into mixture until crumbly.
Pat dough into a 10-inch nonstick pan.
Bake at 350° until set (10 to 15 minutes).
In a medium bowl, beat remaining flour, baking powder, granulated sugar, orange juice, lemon juice and zest, vanilla and eggs.
Pour over crust and bake 12 to 15 minutes or until top is set.
Cool.
Sprinkle with remaining confectioners sugar.
Cut into 48 squares.

title: baked chicken with sour cream gravy
directions: Place chicken in large, covered baking dish.
Cover chicken with chicken soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from the dish.
In the remaining soup, stir in sour cream and pour over chicken.
Serve.
Sour cream is also good on vegetables.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and margarine in a heavy skillet on medium heat until boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend well and turn into a buttered pan and chill.
Cut into pieces to serve.

title: chicken broccoli pot pie
directions: Can make cheese sauce.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Double recipe for 2 pies.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Combine and sift together dry ingredients.
Add well beaten eggs, buttermilk and bacon drippings.
Stir until well blended, adding diced cracklings.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: frozen pickled cabbage
directions: Take cabbage, carrots and mangoes either put into blender to cut or use a slaw cutter.
If using blender, you'll have enough water; if slaw cutter, add some water and let stand also add salt. After 1 hour, drain (squeeze a little to remove some of the saltwater).
Take 2 cups sugar, 1/4 cup water, 1 cup vinegar and 1 teaspoon celery seed and boil for 1 minute and cool at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together and freeze in container. Makes about 2 pints.
Thaw when ready to use.

title: banana bread(yields 1 loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, egg and oil.
Add applesauce and vanilla.
Sift together flour and soda.
Mix everything together, then add mashed bananas.
Spray loaf pan. Pour in mix.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or pour into muffin tin and bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: apple dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Blend in nuts.
Dip apple wedges.

title: spread bread
directions: Mix all together. Spread over bread. Sprinkle garlic salt on top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soup with the cups of water.
Add Rice-A-Roni fried rice, adding the seasoning packet that came with it last.
Pour into a deep casserole dish.
Place the chicken on top of the soup and rice mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately one hour or until the chicken is cooked.

title: pizza swiss steak
directions: Cut the steak into 6 serving sized pieces. Combine the flour, salt and pepper and pound into steak. Pour the oil in a skillet and brown the meat slowly on both sides. Transfer to a 12x7 baking dish.

title: cheese ball delight
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and hand mix evenly. Sprinkle paprika over the top of entire cheese ball.
Cover with Saran Wrap and place in refrigerator.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix well and serve with Wheat Thins.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add melted butter.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes or until firm.

title: friendship cake
directions: Use one gallon jar, 1 1/2 cups starter and 2 1/2 cups sugar and 29 ounce can sliced peaches, slightly chopped.
Set with loose lid.
Stir daily for 10 days.
Add 12 ounce can chunked pineapple and 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir for another 10 days.
On 20th day, add 10 ounce jar maraschino cherries and 29 ounce can fruit cocktail and 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir well for 10 more days.
On 30th day, drain and give away starter to a friend.
Bake 50 minutes or until done in 350° oven in large pan that has been greased and floured.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
In a 2 1/2-quart bowl, layer pudding, vanilla wafers and banana slices.
Repeat layers twice, ending with pudding.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grilled reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread 6 slices of bread with dressing.
Top each with 1 slice cheese, 1 tablespoon sauerkraut, sliced corned beef and bread. Butter top and bottoms of sandwiches.
Grill on both sides until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: cobbler
directions: Slice fresh or canned fruit onto bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan. Cover with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Mix remaining ingredients for batter.
Spread batter by spoonfuls over fruit.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with cream or whipped topping.

title: spiced raisin bars
directions: Cook raisins in 1 cup water.
Cool.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients and the raisins and water.
Spread on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breast in 1-inch pieces.
Dip in honey mustard or Italian salad dressing.
Roll in crushed flake cereal.

title: cheesy whipped potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until fork-tender. Mash potatoes to get the lumps out. Add the remaining ingredients. (Reserve 1/4 cup cheese and 1 slice of bacon.)
Beat on medium-high until whipped. Transfer to your baking dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese and bacon on top. Refrigerate.

title: homestyle butterfly pork chops
directions: Sprinkle steak seasoning liberally on outside of chops.
Season according to taste (pepper, salt and garlic).
Mix stuffing according to directions.
Stuff chops with stuffing.
Use toothpicks to hold together.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 400°.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Brown hamburger.
Add onion (chopped), salt, pepper and oregano; sprinkle red pepper to flavor.
Pour spaghetti and hamburger sauce into a greased casserole bowl.
Mix together.
Bake 2 to 3 hours at 300°.

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Combine tapioca, orange and vanilla pudding with hot water. Cook until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Let cool completely then fold in oranges and one package of whipped topping.
Chill until set.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Cool and peel.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange in 12 x 8 x 2-inch greased dish.

title: cherry pineapple fluff
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients and chill overnight.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in with jello and chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook and stir together until mixture thickens. Drop on wax paper.
Be sure to let cool!

title: green bean bake
directions: In casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper; stir in beans and 1/2 onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with rest of onions; bake 5 minutes.

title: cream of mushroom pork chops
directions: Lightly season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides.
Take out of pan and set aside.
In same pan, lightly saute sliced onion and green pepper.
Stir in can of cream of mushroom soup; take off stove.
In casserole dish, place pork chops; spoon onions, peppers and soup over chops.
Cover and place into oven and bake for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: barbecue beef cups
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Spray Pam cooking spray in muffin pan. Shape biscuits into muffin pan.
Cook ground beef until brown. Drain.
Add barbecue sauce to taste.
Mix. Put about 1 1/2 tablespoons meat in biscuits.
Add shredded cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until ready.

title: fruit salad
directions: Open and drain all the fruit (except cherries) and set aside. Keep the juice (about 3 cups) plus 1/2 cup of orange juice.
Open the pudding, add the 3 1/2 cups juice and cook as you would with milk.
Cool the pudding.
Drain the cherries, rinse them with cold water so the color won't mix through the other fruit.
Slice the bananas over the drained fruit and cherries, then pour the tapioca pudding over.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: homemade cottage cheese
directions: Stir dry milk into 3 3/4 cup water; add buttermilk.
Let set in covered container at room temperature for about 16 to 18 hours. The cheese should be thick and the curd and whey separated.

title: cheesy stuffed eggplant
directions: Wash eggplants; cut in halves lengthwise.
Remove pulp, leaving a 1/4 inch shell; set shells aside.
Cut pulp into 1/2 inch cubes.
Saute eggplant, beef, onion, tomato and garlic until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper and oregano.

title: cornmeal dumplings
directions: Sift together ingredients.
Add just enough milk to form a soft dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into broth.
Cover and simmer over low heat 15 minutes.
Dumplings will get soggy if you lift the lid before they are done.

title: tomato aspic(served at women's club meeting and bridge party)
directions: Heat 1 cup of tomato juice, add to jello and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining cup of tomato juice and seasonings; pour into mold.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes to 1 hour or until desired consistency.
Process in jars.
I use a water bath for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: jiffy spaghetti
directions: Brown meat slightly in fat in skillet at 360°.
Add tomato sauce, water, tomato juice and seasonings from spaghetti package. Bring to a boil and stir to blend.
Break spaghetti into sauce. When steaming freely, turn control to 220° and cook about 30 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (included in spaghetti package).
Serves 6.

title: fish creole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet, cook green pepper, onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour tomato mix over fillets.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until fish is tender.

title: grilled ham steak
directions: In a small
saucepan, add the preserves, mustard, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cook while stirring, about 3 minutes over low heat. Make small
cuts in fat around ham.
Grill 6 inches above coals for about
to
10 minutes per side.
Brush with glaze during the last few minutes of grilling.

title: indian corn stew
directions: Melt oleo in heavy skillet.
Add onions and green peppers. Cook until soft.
Add meat and brown well.
Stirring frequently, add soup, salt, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: french dandelion wine
directions: Let the dandelions soak 2 days.
Strain and add all other ingredients.
Cover with cheesecloth and let set 2 weeks.
Stir everyday so the yeast works.
Strain and bottle lightly.
Wait 3 weeks and seal well.
Good luck.
Very good.

title: old settlers' baked beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onions.
Add and mix all but beans. Drain beans only slightly.
Add and mix them in.
Bake all at 350° for 1 hour.

title: good and easy marinade
directions: Marinate meat (wonderful on venison or deer, as well as beef) for 1 to 8 hours.
Quick-fry.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Cook onions and celery in butter until tender.
Combine with salmon.
Add soup, cheese and rice.
Turn into 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Chill juices and combine in bowl over block of ice.
Add club soda, stir lightly to blend. Garnish with orange slices.
If desired, add 1 bottle (fifth) of white wine or liquor.
Makes 24 to 32 punch cup servings.

title: chicken or turkey supreme
directions: Cook rices in broth.
Saute vegetables until transparent (about 5 minutes).
Add chicken or turkey, soup, water chestnuts, peas and seasonings.
Add rice and bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for about 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: red clam dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix together cocktail sauce, celery and clams (drained).
Pour over blocks of cream cheese.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind orange, apple, nuts and cranberries in food chopper. Add sugar and let stand 30 minutes.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and chill 30 minutes.
Combine ground ingredients with jello; stir well and chill.
Happy Thanksgiving!

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole and lay chicken pieces on top of that.
Pour soups over chicken. Sprinkle dry onion soup on top.
No salt needs to be added as the soups and mix are enough.
Bake 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Shape mixture into (1-2 in.) meatballs.
Place meatballs on broiler pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 min. or until done.
May need to repeat, depending on number of meat balls and oven style.
May serve alone or add favorite sauce.

title: cottage cheese-spinach casserole
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, eggs and flour.
Add American cheese.
Allow spinach to thaw until it can be broken apart in chunks.
Add frozen chunks to mixture.
Cut butter in pieces and combine with mixture.
Add salt.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In large pot, cover chicken with water and cook until tender. Remove from pot and let cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients to chicken stock, adding water if necessary.
Remove chicken from bones and chop in bite size pieces.
Return to pot with vegetables and simmer 30 minutes.
Add 5 to 6 cups egg noodles and cook just until noodles are done.
More water can be added for soup or less and can be served as a main dish.

title: veggie chicken soup
directions: In a large pot, pour broth, chicken and cut veggies; add seasonings and cook until veggies are tender.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix well; spread in a large round dish or 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Top with cut up lettuce, tomatoes and chopped green onions. Top with grated cheese; serve with taco chips.

title: ham casserole
directions: Add buttered cracker crumbs or bread crumbs on top and bake at 325° about 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and fill an unbaked crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 35 minutes at 350° or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add boiling water and margarine.
Cook until thick; add vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: missouri scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Soak raisins, cherries and figs in brandy 15 minutes.
Prepare the cake batter, folding in the soaked fruits, any brandy left in bowl and the remaining ingredients into the batter as directed in Step 3 (1-2-3-4 cake).
Spoon into pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.
If top browns too fast, lay a piece of foil loosely over it.
Cool cake in the pan on rack 10 minutes before turning out onto rack to cool. If you wish, wrap cake in cloth sprinkled with peach brandy.
Place in airtight can and let mellow for a day before serving.

title: pork chops with cabbage
directions: Brown pork chops and remove from boiler.
Wash cabbage and cut into pieces.
Layer cabbage, pork chops and onion.
Add 1/2 cup water and melted butter.
Simmer for approximately 20 minutes.

title: caramel apple cookie pie
directions: Knead flour and cookie dough and put in pizza pan. Bake per directions on cookie dough package. Cool. Mix next four ingredients and put on top. Slice apple and put on top and drizzle with caramel.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed until combined, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until cake pulls away from sides of pan and springs back when lightly touched in center.

title: corn pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add flour, corn, butter, milk and seasonings.
Pour into casserole dish and cover.
Bake 45 minutes in preheated 400° oven.

title: my grandmother's mac 'n cheese(side dish for hot dogs or fish sticks)
directions: In baking dish, mix macaroni, tomato sauce, cumin and onion. Remove onion and save.
Sprinkle top with cheese and garnish with onion.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: aunt fanny's cabin baked squash
directions: Boil, mash and drain squash and onions.
Add 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and 1/2 stick margarine to squash.
Then add all other ingredients except margarine and cracker crumbs.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs and drizzle remaining margarine over top of crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine
all
these
ingredients together and pour into loaf pans,
well
greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt together the caramels and 1/3 cup canned milk.
Mix cake mix powder, 1/3 cup canned milk and melted butter together. Spread one half of cake mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 package chocolate chips over top.
Pour melted caramel mixture over top of that.
Spread evenly if desired.
Crumble other half of cake mixture over top.
Bake for 18 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook hens tender.
Cool and cut into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients, except potatoes, and cook over low fire for 2 or 3 hours.
Add diced potatoes and continue cooking for another hour.
Serve hot with saltine crackers.
Serves 50 people.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Put romaine in bottom of bowl.
Sprinkle salt, sugar and pepper.
Put 1 cup cheese; layer eggs on top of cheese.
Stand some up around sides of bowl also.
Sprinkle a little more salt. Layer 1/2 of the bacon, the leaf lettuce and the peas.
Spread mayonnaise over the top completely to the edge of the bowl.
Put the rest of the cheese, bacon and green onion to top off.
Looks best in a clear bowl.
Make the night before.
Toss just before serving.

title: super meat and potatoes
directions: Mix 1/2 of soup, onion, meat, egg and bread crumbs.
Press in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Frost with mashed potatoes, then add remaining soup and cheese.
Return plate to oven and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: anna brittin's potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and cube potatoes.
Cut celery fine.
Add to potatoes.
Mix with salad dressing.
Add eggs, cubed and carefully mixed in.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook rice and cook hamburger separately.
Clean out inside of peppers; then boil until somewhat tender.
Drain off fat from hamburger; add the sauce and cooked rice.
Cook for 10 minutes. Then fill peppers with mixture and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Put these in casserole pan; bake at 200° until cheese is melted, about 15 minutes.

title: ham and pickle roll-ups
directions: Remove moisture from ham slices and pickles using paper towels.
Spread cream cheese on ham slices.
Place pickle to fit the hams short end and roll in the length.
Form fit. Refrigerate.
Then slice in 1/4-inch pieces and place on dish with toothpicks.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in oven at 300° for 40 minutes, or until done.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Precook beans with minced onion and salt.
Pour into crock-pot and add browned hamburger, ketchup and Brick chili.
Let cook all day or at least 6 hours.

title: wild chile
directions: Cook venison and drain. Place venison, beans, sauce and paste in large pan and simmer. Add peppers and garlic and mix well. Simmer on low heat 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally, adding salt and pepper to taste. Allow to cool and refrigerate for 24 hours. Reheat and simmer for 1 hour. Cool and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Heat and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream powdered sugar and peanut butter until it is crumbly. Set aside.
Stir next 8 ingredients in a saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring just below boiling point.
Bake pie shell until half done, then sprinkle 3/4 of the peanut butter and powdered sugar mixture over shell.
Pour custard into shell.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fish and fries
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange fish fillets in single layer.
Place a layer of fries on top of fish. Combine soup, milk and Miracle Whip in a small bowl and mix well.
Pour over fish and fries.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serve with hot rolls and a green salad.

title: quick, rich, moist coffee cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter.
Break the egg into a measuring cup and add enough milk to make a cup.
Add vanilla.
Stir milk-vanilla mixture into the dry ingredients.
Spoon batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with Honey Bee Glaze.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Reheat for 5 minutes before serving.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
In small mixing bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, water, shortening and egg. Blend well at lowest speed; beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Spread batter in 10 inch deep pie pan.

title: taco dip(requested at all family gatherings!)
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1/2 of taco seasoning.
Spread in pizza pan.
Continue to assemble as if making a pizza.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Grate all vegetables and drain separately on paper towels. Combine other ingredients; beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, salt and lemon juice until creamy.
Add vegetables and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Make sandwiches when ready to serve.

title: bacon dogs
directions: Dip each hot dog into sauce.
Wrap with bacon slice.
Secure with toothpicks.
Grill until bacon is crisp.
Serve on rolls.
Or cook on green sticks over campfire.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Cook for 2 hours at 350°.

title: orange french toast
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, juice and brown sugar.
Beat with a fork until combined.
Transfer the mixture to a pie plate.
Dip bread into egg mixture about 30 seconds on each side or until thoroughly soaked.
In a skillet or on a griddle, fry bread in hot oil over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Serve with syrup.
Makes 5 to 6 slices.
Per slice:
170 calories, 4 grams protein, 30 grams carbohydrates, 4 grams fat, 92 milligrams cholesterol and 177 milligrams sodium.

title: jean's frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip the cream (any brand).
Blend with mayonnaise; add salt. Strain syrup from can of fruit salad and mix the fruit salad with the blended mixture.
Freeze until solid.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken in halves, lengthwise.
Wash, drain and roll at once in flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Dip in combined eggs and milk and roll in cracker crumbs.
Heat shortening and dry.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Temperature is 385°.
Time:
15 to 20 minutes.

title: tofu dip or no-egg salad
directions: Mash tofu to cottage cheese consistency.
Add seasonings, being sure to include the three "S's" (something salty; something sour; something sticky) to bind the mixture.
Mix in chopped onion.
Dip in ready to eat, or let sit for stronger flavor.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into three 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix the sugar, Karo syrup, evaporated milk or half and half cream and oleo and cook for 8 minutes (or until holds a firm ball) after it reaches a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla and food coloring.
Beat until creamy. Add the peanuts. Drop on waxed paper into patties.

title: shortcake
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Combine the egg and light cream; add all at once to flour mixture, stirring with fork just to moisten.
Spread dough in a greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan or greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan, building up edges slightly.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool slightly.

title: garden club chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the chicken, celery, grapes, nuts, onion, salt, mayonnaise and cream.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce or greens and garnish with olives or pickles.
Serves 6.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Spray flat pan with Pam.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Crush tomatoes; set aside.
Mix juice from tomatoes with dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in the crushed tomatoes.
Mix and pour total mixture into greased pan.
Bake in 400° oven for about 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cut into squares and serve warm.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows with butter.
Add box of crushed graham crackers and cherries (juice and all).
Add pecans.
Add raisins and coconut.
Put in a pound cake pan and chill before serving. After it's chilled, take out of pan and slice.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes.
Let cool and peel.
Beat potatoes with 1/3 cup margarine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in crock-pot 4 to 9 hours or place in casserole dish and microwave on Medium heat for 30 minutes.

title: 3-hour buns
directions: Boil Crisco and 2 cups water.
Add other ingredients and beat. Add as much flour as needed.
Let rise until double.
Punch down.
Form into buns.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: In colander, thaw spinach and press out water until it almost feels dry.
Add ingredients and mix.

title: coffee cake
directions: Heavily grease a Bundt or angel cake pan with Crisco or shortening.
Roll cake pan with chopped pecans until sides and bottom are coated.
Place frozen rolls along bottom.
Melt butter or margarine and add brown sugar, cinnamon and butterscotch pudding.
Pour over rolls.
Cover with towel and allow to sit overnight.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Allow to cool 5 to 10 minutes before dumping on plate.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: Drain mixed fruit; do not save juice.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine Tang and instant pudding.
Add pineapple juice to dry mixture; stir.
Add fruit and toss.
Garnish with cherries.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in angel food cake.
Spread into an oblong baking dish.
Mix together strawberries and glaze.
Spread over cake mixture.
Chill.

title: albondigas(spanish for meatballs)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into large or small meatballs.
Cover with flour and fry in oil until golden brown. Remove meatballs from oil and prepare Salsa.

title: italian heros
directions: In skillet, place sausage, onion, pepper and 1/2 cup water. Cover and cook 25 minutes until done; drain.
Serve on Hero rolls, adding spaghetti sauce, if desired.

title: heavenly fudge
directions: Using
a
heavy saucepan, bring the first 3 ingredients to
a boil; boil for 4 1/2 minutes.
Melt the chocolate chips and chocolate bars.
Add chocolate, wax, nuts and marshmallow cream. Mix
until cool; pour out in pans.	Cut before it sets too hard.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder and soda together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all filling ingredients together thoroughly. Spread filling evenly over tortillas. Roll. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate for several hours. Unwrap and cut into slices. Serve with salsa. Makes 50 pinwheels.

title: chili-bean dip
directions: Combine ingredients and whip briefly.
Place over low heat, stirring frequently, until hot and cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Beat until fluffy. Alternately add bananas, nuts, flour and liquid.
Beat until smooth. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Cook peas and rice.
Reserve.
Cook vegetables in butter 6 to 8 minutes.
Add peas, rice and tomatoes.
Heat through.
Add seasonings.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips in top of double boiler; let cool.
When cool, add marshmallows and chopped nuts.
Stir all together.
Spread coconut on wax paper and place mixture on coconut.
Form into a roll and roll in coconut.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Cut into slices.
Very pretty.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add sugar.
Add enough water to make 2 gallons.

title: four chip double nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and grease 12 muffin cups or preheat oven to 350° and grease 48 mini muffin cups.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Combine graham crackers, butter and powdered sugar; mix well and put into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Then combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar and beat with egg beater or electric mixer. Spread over mixture of graham crackers and bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Let get cold and top with can of cherries and refrigerate. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Can be prepared 1 or 2 days before.

title: frozen banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until dissolved.
Cool and add the remaining
ingredients except lemon-lime beverage.
Freeze for 24 hours.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving and add lemon-lime drink.
Yield:
60 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients (except cracker crumbs) and fold into broccoli.
Place cracker crumbs on top and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: garlic chicken with rice pilaf
directions: Cook chicken, garlic, pepper and oregano in olive oil until lightly browned on each side. (15-20 min.)
Prepare rice as directed. In a casserole dish spread cooked rice on bottom.
Place lightly steamed broccoli on top of rice.
Next, place chicken on top. Sprinkle cheese on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 min.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Saute chopped onions in margarine in the microwave until onions are clear (approximately 4 minutes).
Add cream cheese; soften in the microwave.
Add crabmeat, seasonings and bread crumbs.
Serve hot.

title: ann's skillet chicken special
directions: Brown the onion in a skillet with just a small amount of vegetable oil.
Add the chicken breasts and brown.
In a bowl, mix the soups with the milk.
Blend well and then add the spices.
Add this liquid mixture to the skillet with the chicken and simmer over low heat for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Serves 4 to 6, depending on number of chicken breasts.

title: quiche(a low carb recipe)
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Spray pie or quiche pan with Pam. In skillet melt butter and cook onions three minutes and add mushrooms and cook until softened.
Set aside.
Combine the eggs, egg yolks, heavy cream, and sour cream in bowl with whisk.
Add cooked onion mixture and the rest of the ingredients and blend well.
Pour into pan and cook 40 to 45 minutes or until set in the center and golden brown on top.
Cool at least 10 minutes before serving.
Yields:
12 servings.
2 grams carbs per serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix
sugar,
eggs,
vegetable oil and pumpkin together. Sift all
dry
ingredients
together and add to first mixture. Grease and
flour two loaf pans or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15
minutes
Cool for 10 minutes on rack before removing from pan.

title: dessert salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill.
When partially set, fold in softened cream cheese, fruits, nuts and cream. Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
I use my food processor to make it smooth and creamy, but it can be mixed by hand for more texture.

title: jimmy's pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in 5-quart electric freezer. Add ice and salt to freezer.
Freeze until firm.

title: coco cake
directions: Bake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crab butter
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Add lemon juice, garlic and worcestershire sauce and mix well. Add onion and mix well. Stir in crab gently by hand. Chill mixture at least two hours.
Spread mixture onto a serving plate. Pour cocktail sauce over the top. Serve with crackers.

title: southwestern tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: In large skillet, stir together all ingredients except Cheddar cheese.
Add 1 cup water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender and most of liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: melody nixon's spinach casserole
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter.
Add cottage cheese (whiz through blender, if desired) and spices to sauteed mixture.
Drain and chop spinach. Add to cottage cheese mixture.
Stir in drained noodles.
Mix well and pour in greased baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine or shortening.
Add eggs; mix together. Add cocoa, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Take out pan; pour marshmallows on top.
Put back in oven for 10 minutes.
Let cake cool for 20 minutes.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prick top of warm brownies at 1-inch intervals, using a meat fork and brush with liqueur, if desired. Let cool and crumble.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of salted water; drain and mash. Mix with next five ingredients and 1/2 package of stuffing.
Take other half of stuffing mix and blend with margarine.
Sprinkle over top of casserole and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini with veal and cheese filling
directions: Rinse zucchini; pat dry.
Trim ends.
With apple corer, hollow out center, leaving a shell no wider than 1/4 inch.
Finely chop enough zucchini pulp to make 1 cup; reserve remainder for another use.
With fork, score zucchini lengthwise; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: savory potato-cheese soup
directions: Put first 4 ingredients and 1 teaspoon of salt in kettle. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 15 minutes. Melt butter and blend in flour. Add remaining salt, pepper, mustard, steak sauce and milk. Cook until smooth and thickened. Add remaining ingredients and potato mixture. Simmer for a few minutes.

title: shrimp salad(camarones en salpicon)
directions: Wash shrimp thoroughly.
Bring water to a boil in large saucepan.
Add 1 tablespoon of lime juice, bay leaf, peppercorns and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Drop shrimp into boiling water.
Cook 4 minutes.
Drain shrimp, reserving liquid.
Peel shrimp; slit backs and remove veins.
Place shrimp in large bowl.
Cover with reserved water; chill.
Before serving, drain shrimp thoroughly.
Mix drained shrimp with chile, tomato, green onions and cilantro. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon lime juice and salt and pepper to taste. Stir.
Arrange lettuce leaves on 4 plates.
Spoon shrimp mixture evenly onto lettuce leaves.
Mound 1 tablespoon of mayonnaise beside shrimp; garnish with lemon wedge.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients until completely dissolved.
Spoon about 1/3 mixture on bottom of baking dish.
Place all of peaches next, then slowly pour rest of mixture on top of peaches.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ethel's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients, shape into loaf, wrap in foil.
Put 3 tablespoons ketchup on top.
Add a little water.
Bake until done (approximately 2 hours).

title: lite egg custard
directions: Put in microwave for 6 minutes.
Serves 1 person.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: deluxe angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and powdered sugar together 4 times; set aside. Add salt to egg whites, beat whites to a coarse foam with electric mixer at medium speed.
Add cream of tartar and flavorings.
Beat until whites just begin to peak.
Gradually add sugar,
a tablespoon at a time and continue beating until moist, fine, glossy textured and forms stiff peaks.
Using a wire egg beater, gently fold in flour and sugar, about 1/4 cup at a time.
Spoon gently into a 10-inch tube pan.
With knife, cut through batter to break up large air bubbles.
Bake on lower rack of oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Invert pan over bottle until cold.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
In another bowl sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture until well blended.
Stir the black walnuts in last.
Shape dough into logs about 2 inches in diameter, wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until firm.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees, slice the dough logs into 1/2 inch slices and place on baking sheets.
Bake in preheated oven for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: golden wassail drink(for christmas or thanksgiving)
directions: Combine all in large kettle or crock-pot.
Simmer and serve hot in crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Take chicken fillet and put on top a slice of ham and Provolone cheese in long strips, 1/2-inch wide, then add salt and pepper to taste.
Roll in flour, then in beaten eggs, then into bread crumb mixture.
Fry until lightly brown, then put in oven in a baking pan or casserole and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Sprinkle on coconut, chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over top.
Sprinkle nuts evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: spiced iced coffee
directions: Pour 3 cups of very strong hot coffee over 2 cinnamon sticks, 4 whole cloves and 4 whole allspice.
Let stand 1 hour.
Pour over ice in 4 tall glasses.
Add cream and sugar for delicious spiced iced coffee.

title: spinach puffs
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a small pan; bring to boil and cook 10 minutes.
Drain well; squeeze to remove excess liquid. Combine spinach mixture and remaining ingredients; stir well. Cover and chill 2 hours.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls; place 4 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Chill at least 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm. Yields 4 dozen.

title: bourbon and rum brownies with pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Omit water called for on brownie package (you may have to add 1 tablespoon water to mixture before baking). Combine brownie mix, egg, chocolate packet and pecans.
Recommend a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake according to package instructions. Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with bourbon.
Cool completely.
Combine 1/2 cup softened oleo or butter, sugar and rum.
Spread evenly over brownies.
Chill about an hour.

title: roquefort and pecan dressing
directions: Blend together all ingredients with salt and pepper to taste. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add beaten egg.
Sprinkle yeast into the warm water; stir until dissolved and add to mixture.
Add flour and blend well.

Cover and place in the refrigerator for at least 4 hours. About three hours before using, roll out 1/2 inch thick and cut with a biscuit cutter; brush tops with melted butter; fold over into pocketbook shape; or pinch off about a 1 1/2 inch ball; roll and shape with your hands.
(You can make rolls larger or smaller if you want to.)
Place on greased pan and allow to rise at room temperature for about 3 hours.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes This batter will keep for several days in the refrigerator.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: auction colonel corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill. Keep in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: wendy's marinade
directions: Mix ingredients together well, making sure to dissolve sugar. Best when used for short ribs.
Use 4 pounds ribs for 4 people. Score ribs.
Marinate overnight.
Cook on grill for 45 minutes to 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.
Start with bone side down. Baste as needed.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Important:
Do not use an electric mixer.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add coconut and chopped pecans.
Cook until golden brown; stir often.
Combine cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Layer 1/4 of cream cheese mixture in shell. Then layer 1/4 of caramel topping; then add 1/4 of coconut and pecans.
Repeat, ending with coconut and pecans.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix pineapple and powdered sugar together in a loaf pan.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Freeze until solid. Remove from freezer and break into small chunks with fork.
Whip with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour back into pan and refreeze.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Measure 2 cups broth into 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Cover and microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add potatoes and onions.
Cover and microwave on High 12 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Combine instant milk with remaining 1 cup broth.
Stir until dissolved. Add milk, margarine and pepper to potatoes.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: plantation coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage and carrot; set aside.
Combine sour cream and remaining ingredients.
Pour over
cabbage mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: golden carrot salad
directions: In a serving bowl, toss together the carrots, orange segments and parsley.
Combine orange juice and honey and pour over salad. Serve in lettuce lined salad bowl.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve this salad with broiled chicken, roast duck or game.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and heat one hour in a 1-quart crock-pot before serving with your choice of crackers.
(I have used no-fat cheese and mayonnaise, and it isn't bad, although it is not as good as the original.)

title: debbie's banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Mash bananas with rotary beater or fork.
Add lemon juice and mix. Cream shortening and sugar with electric mixer at medium speed. Add eggs and beat thoroughly until light and fluffy (4 minutes, beating in all).
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Mix after each addition.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire racks.
Wrap in foil or plastic.
Freezes well.

title: peanut candy roll
directions: Chop nuts (1/2 cup) finely chopped and 1/2 cup coarsely chopped.
Blend butter, corn syrup, maple flavor and salt.
