Stir in sugar all at once.
Knead until smooth.
Add a few drops of water if necessary.
Knead in finely chopped nuts.
Shape into 2 nut rolls, brush with a little corn syrup and roll in coarse nuts. Wrap and chill.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Form into loaf.
Put in loaf pan. Pour remaining tomatoes and green chilies on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Separate eggs; beat whites stiff.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, etc. Fold egg whites in; put in freezer and fill to top with milk.

title: easy oven "fries"
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Wash potatoes and leave skin in.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Cut each half into 4 wedges.
Combine all ingredients (except Pam).
Dip cut sides of each wedge into cheese mixture.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Place wedges skin side down on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown. Leftovers zap well in microwave.

title: tomato pilaf
directions: Boil rice in water as directed but add the bouillon cube so the rice will absorb the flavor.
Fry the zucchini in 1 tablespoon butter until slightly brown.
Combine the tomatoes in a separate pot and bring to a boil.
Add butter and salt and pepper.
Combine the zucchini and the tomato sauce.
Add the cooked rice and bring to a final boil.
Season with salt and pepper as desired and serve.
Serves 2 to 4.
This can be reheated using tomato juice to moisten.

title: strawberry champagne
directions: You will also need nonstick spray coating.

title: joan's sunday roast and yorkshire pudding
directions: Cook roast in slow oven until well done and brown (275° approximately 3 hours).
Mix salt and flour and add the milk gradually to make a smooth paste.
Add eggs and beat two minutes with a rotary beater.
Cover bottom of two bread pans with beef drippings from the roast.
Pour the mixture in pans 1/2 inch deep. Bake at 450° for twenty minutes.
Cut in squares for serving.

title: mulled cider
directions: Put cider in large pan.
Put all the spices in large tea bag, strainer or cheesecloth; boil for 10 to 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Can be stored and reheated later.
Serve hot with orange slices as floaters.
Makes about 10 to 16 cups.

title: drop cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients of flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar; set aside.
Cream brown and white sugar and oleo.
Mix in oil, egg and flavorings.
Mix in dry ingredients, then quick oats and then Rice Krispies.
Add chocolate chips and coconut if desired.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet, very lightly press down a little.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown on edges, about 9 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: party ham sandwiches
directions: Mix onions, poppy seed, mustard and soft margarine.
Layer cheese, ham and onion mixture on rolls.
Place rolls on baking sheet.
Place tops of rolls over cheese, ham and onion mixture. Place in a 350° oven and bake for 20 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: pickled squash
directions: Cover squash with salt and crushed ice.
Mix and let stand 3 hours.
Drain water.
Combine all ingredients and pour over squash.
Heat to a boil and pack in jars and seal.

title: whole wheat bagels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in honey, salt and 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead 10 minutes.

title: savory peas
directions: Melt butter slowly in saucepan with tight fitting cover.
Add unthawed peas and remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 8 minutes or until the peas are just tender.
Be sure not to overcook.

title: sloppy beef
directions: Brown ground beef in a frying pan.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Spoon over toasted buns. Can double or triple this recipe.

title: candied sweet potatoes(yields 8 servings)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until fork-tender.
Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice in a saucepan; stir in pineapple juice, syrup, orange juice and butter.
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Arrange half of the potatoes in
a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour half of the sugar mixture over the potatoes.
Repeat in layers.
Sprinkle pecans over the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Fold in whipped topping, pineapple and nuts.
Pour in pie shells and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: bundt bread
directions: Layer biscuits overlapping in bottom of Teflon Bundt pan. Melt margarine.
Add Parmesan cheese, dill weed and lemon juice. Pour over biscuit ring.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Turn onto plate.
Pull apart when serving.

title: children's party punch
directions: Mix water with jello as is standard procedure in preparing jello.
Add the orange and chill until cold.
Add the ginger ale and ice cubes before serving.

title: patty's potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until they are almost done.
Combine all other ingredients in saucepan.
Heat on low heat until cheese melts. Put drained potatoes in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix above ingredients in a medium size bowl.
Transfer to a buttered casserole and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes. Serve with Melba rounds.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine butter, sugar and water in large saucepan.
Cook, stirring frequently, until candy reaches 300° (hard crack) on candy thermometer.
Quickly stir in vanilla and carefully pour into greased jelly roll pan.
While still warm, place unwrapped Hershey bars on top.
Spread evenly when chocolate melts.
You may sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
When cool and chocolate has set, break into pieces.

title: barbara's banana muffins
directions: Hand mix all ingredients; bake in muffin tins at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt twice.
Set oven at 400° and prepare cookie pans.
Cream shortening and blend in sugar.
Mix in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour to form stiff dough.
Chill.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar and bake for 10 minutes.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown steak and onions in butter.
Add 1/2 cup water and simmer over low heat 45 minutes.
Add soup and simmer 15 minutes more.
Add sour cream and mushrooms and heat through until boiling. Serve over noodles.

title: french pork pie
directions: *Sweet basil may be substituted for cinnamon.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix according to directions, but add vanilla, coconut flavoring and coconut.
Mix evaporated milk, water and powdered sugar and pour over hot cake, after pricking holes in cake with fork.
Cool cake.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut, then refrigerate.

title: family style french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and cinnamon; spread in a greased 15 x 10 baking pan.
Set aside.
Combine eggs and milk in a shallow dish; place bread in dish and soak for 5 minutes, turning once.
Place bread over sugar mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve brown sugar side up; dust with confectioners sugar.

title: carol's squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, steam squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain well and mash.
Set aside.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: In a small bowl, combine soups and milk.
In a shallow baking dish, layer alternately chicken and broccoli.
Pour soup mixture over each layer.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).
Good with tossed salad.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: easy sesame chicken
directions: Combine first 4 items.
Melt butter with the tarragon.
Add lemon juice.
Dip chicken pieces in butter mixture.
Roll in potato flake mixture.
Place skin side up in shallow pan so pieces do not touch.
Bake in 350° oven until tender (about 1 1/2 hours). Serves 4 to 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and mix with sauteed onions and all other ingredients.
Place into a pot; stir and bring to boil. Then turn on low to simmer at least 1 hour to bring out flavor.

title: miss mary bobo's pineapple-cheddar casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Arrange pineapple on bottom of a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir together the flour and sugar and sprinkle on pineapple.
Drizzle the reserved juice over all.
Top with the grated cheese.
Mix the crushed crackers and melted butter.
Spread over cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown in skillet hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer in skillet about 20 minutes.

title: mashed potato fried cakes
directions: Cream potatoes, sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix with former ingredients slowly. Roll to about 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with fried cake cutter.
Fry in hot grease at 360° for about one minute on each side.

title: ham roll-up pinwheels
directions: Lay out one flour tortilla. Lay one piece of ham on top of tortilla. Layer Ranch dip on ham and sprinkle some black olives on, then green onions, then cheese. Roll as tightly as you can, then slice it about 1-inch thick. Chill and serve.

title: tropical fruit dip
directions: In medium bowl combine mayonnaise, sour cream, lime juice, honey, cumin and Tabasco sauce; mix well.
Stir in coconut. Cover.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve with cut-up fresh fruit.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: country chicken
directions: Melt butter in a deep, flat dish. Salt and pepper the chicken lightly; roll in the melted butter and arrange in a single layer in the dish. Sprinkle rice over chicken and add water slowly; sprinkle onion soup mix over rice. Cover tightly and bake a 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fake apple pie
directions: Divide your favorite pastry into two parts.
Line pastry pan and pour apple mixture into the pan.
Roll top crust and slit. Cover pie and seal edges.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: savory green beans
directions: Wash and string beans.
Set aside.
In 4-quart saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter and saute onion and peppers about 5 minutes or until tender.
Add water and seasonings.
Bring to a boil and add green beans.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and continue cooking until beans are tender, about 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix in bowl with fork until it forms a ball.
Put in pie pan and use hands to pat to cover bottom and sides of pan.
Makes one 9 or 10-inch pan crust.

title: plain cake layers for strawberry cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, oil, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 300° in 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans about 30 minutes or until done.
Cool well before icing.
Take a drinking straw and punch holes in the layers.
Put strawberries on first and let soak into cake.

title: eggless cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour and cocoa together; add alternately with milk.
Add vinegar.
Add soda in hot water.
Bake at 400°.

title: peach crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together peaches, raisins, honey and ginger in casserole that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix together cereal, coconut and cinnamon. Sprinkle over peach mixture.
Drizzle butter over all.
Bake 20 minutes until hot.

title: beef stew
directions: Dredge meat with flour and brown on all sides in shortening in Dutch oven pot.
Add 2 teaspoons salt, the pepper and water. Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours until meat is almost tender.
Add rest of ingredients except peas and simmer for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Season and sprinkle with peas.
Makes 6 servings.

title: amish fruit jam
directions: Combine fruit and sugar.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Add Jell-O.
Pour into sterilized hot jars and water. Boil both for 10 minutes until jars seal.

title: ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first six ingredients; beat well. Stir in ice cream.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze for several hours or overnight.
Let pie stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream and nuts.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: sticky buns
directions: Sprinkle first 3 ingredients in bottom of tube pan.
Arrange rolls in pan; sprinkle with pudding.
Melt 7 tablespoons of butter; mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls.
Let rise overnight, uncovered.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn out of pan immediately onto plate.
Serve.
Delicious!
Great for Christmas morning.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: heavenly hash cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and marshmallows with sugar.
Let set overnight in fridge.
When ready to serve, add pecans and whipped cream.
Stir.
Very pretty.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Stir lard, salt, sugar and boiling water together until it is a creamy mass and well blended.
Then stir in flour.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
This crust is good kept in refrigerator for several weeks and can also be frozen.

title: punch
directions: Chill Hawaiian Punch and lemonade or orange juice concentrate. When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Run it down the side of bowl. May add liquor and ice ring.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the milk, vegetable oil and vanilla until smooth.
Spread in an ungreased 9-inch square baking pan.

title: orange-cashew chicken
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons of orange juice.
Mix with soy sauce. Set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add chicken, cashews and garlic.
Cook 2 minutes on hot heat.
Remove chicken and cashews. Heat remaining oil in the same pan.
Add onion and snow peas. Stir-fry 3 minutes.
Put chicken and cashews back in pan.
Stir in sauce.
Cook long enough to coat with sauce.
Add mandarin oranges. Heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: batter pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk into a batter. Melt the butter into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour batter over butter in baking dish.
Pour the fruit over the batter.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Pour the apple cider and maple syrup into a large stainless steel saucepan. Place the cinnamon sticks, cloves, allspice berries, orange peel and lemon peel in the center of a washed square of cheesecloth; fold up the sides of the cheesecloth to enclose the bundle, then tie it up with a length of kitchen string. Drop the spice bundle into the cider mixture. Place the saucepan over moderate heat for five to ten minutes, or until the cider is very hot but not boiling. Remove the cider from the heat. Discard the spice bundle. Ladle the cider into big cups or mugs, adding a fresh cinnamon stick to each serving if desired.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash
bananas
and soda thoroughly.
Mix other ingredients and then
combine with soda and banana mixture.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: green tomato spice bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add other ingredients
in order given.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Let batter raise for 10 minutes.
Smooth top of loaves, then make a slit along top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cut sausage and chuck into chunks.
Mince garlic, chop onion and simmer all ingredients until thick (one or two hours).

title: roland's favorite beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Coat meat cubes in seasoned flour.
Brown in hot shortening in Dutch oven.
Add soup, 2 1/2 cups water, onion and basil.
Cover and bake in 375° oven about 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots and wine.
Cover and bake another hour or until tender.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Cook beef lightly, drain fat.
Add onion and garlic, cook until soft.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 hour.
Serve over hot spaghetti.
Serves 4.

title: olive balls
directions: Mix flour, oleo and cheese.
Wrap around olives.
Can be frozen.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: belgium meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, green pepper, meal, seasonings, milk and egg; blend well.
Form into 12 to 20 balls.
Roll in flour.
Brown in hot shortening.
Add remaining flour to tomatoes and pour over meat balls.
Cover and bake in 450° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mint meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Two egg whites beaten with a pinch of cream of tartar.
When very stiff, slowly add 2/3 cup sugar.
Add green food coloring to desired color.
Fold in mint chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Turn off oven and place cookies in and leave overnight.

title: cod creole
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil about 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, bay leaf, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, let fish stand at room temperature to thaw slightly, then cut in 1 inch cubes.
Add to sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: baked apple doughnuts
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and sugar.
Stir in egg, milk and apples.
Fill greased baking tins 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan.
Roll in 1/2 cup melted butter first, then in mixture of 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a mold or a bowl and chill.

title: layered jello salad
directions: Empty jello and Knox gelatine in separate bowls.
Dissolve jello with 1 cup boiling water and Knox with 1/2 cup cold water. Pour 1 flavor of jello in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator until set, about 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple rolls
directions: Line 2 muffin pans with paper cups.
Set aside.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Working with half of the dough at a time, knead the dough ten times on a floured surface.
Roll dough out into a rectangular shape 1/4-inch thick.
Spread melted margarine over the dough.
Mix equal parts of cinnamon and sugar.
Sprinkle generously on the entire dough surface.
Spoon the chopped apples about 1 inch from the long edge along the entire length of the rectangle.
Roll from the apple edge.
Cut about 1 inch intervals.
Place in paper cups.
Baste with a little milk.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: joyce's first pineapple cake(date may 10, 1948)
directions: Mix together ingredients and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Heat in double boiler (do not cook) 1/2 cup white sugar and 1/2 cup corn syrup.
Add peanut butter, Rice Krispies, corn flakes, salt and vanilla.
Smooth into 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: fruit bars (molasses bar)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine sugar through corn syrup (first 9 ingredients) and cream well. Add three eggs and blend well. Add honey and molasses. Add raisins and blend. Add flour and blend well. Spread mixture on parchment lined cookie sheet. Bake one egg and moisten top of egg wash. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool. Cut into 2 x 4-inch rectangles.

title: key lime pie
directions: Stir ingredients together until smooth. Pour in graham cracker shell. Bake at 325° or 25 to 28 minutes.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salt. Pour over cabbage and green pepper. Let stand for 1/2 hour or longer to develop flavors. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy pasta salad
directions: Cook shells until done and drain.
Chop fine the olives, salami, pepperoni, cheese, onions, celery, green peppers and tomatoes.
Combine with shells.
Mix together pepper, sugar, oregano, vinegar, oil and salt.
Pour over shell mixture.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Heat, but do not boil, vinegar and celery salt.
Cook eggs and peel while still warm.
Add onion.
Pour vinegar mixture over eggs and onions.
Let stand for 2 days.
Better if left to stand longer.

title: snow-top chocolate cookies
directions: Place chocolate and shortening in a small saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until melted.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes in jacket.
Add celery, green onions, Italian dressing and Cavender's Greek seasoning; salt and pepper to taste. Toss thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight and add Miracle Whip as desired and serve.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over Rice Chex and pur in large plastic bag and add powdered sugar.
Shake real good.
Mix will look like a mess when you put into bag, but sugar coats each piece.

title: steak soup plaza iii
directions: Place the butter in a soup pot and allow to melt without browning.
Add flour and stir to form a smooth paste.
Cook the mixture (roux) over medium heat, without browning, for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the consomme to the roux and stir until smooth and lightly thickened.
Bring to a full boil.
Add the fresh vegetables, tomatoes, Kitchen Bouquet, bouillon and pepper; allow to regain a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer until the vegetables are just barely tender.
(This should take about 20 to 30 minutes.) Add the frozen vegetables and the browned ground steak.
Simmer an additional 15 minutes, or long enough that the flavors become well blended.

title: cole slaw
directions: Pour salad dressing mixture over cabbage mixture; mix well.

title: cornlight bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients, then add buttermilk and bacon drippings.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 25 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Pour off excess grease.
Stir in green chilies, pinto beans and chicken soup.
Break up Doritos and put in baking dish.
Pour meat mixture over Doritos.
Then spoon the cheese soups over mixture and put in 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: company tuna bake
directions: Blend cheese and soup with mixer.
Add tuna, pimiento, onion, mustard, milk and macaroni.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket (fat side up) in a 9 x 13-inch aluminum pan. Cut celery and carrots in half or thirds and place on top of meat. Use celery leaves also; sprinkle chopped onion, parsley and garlic on top of this.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with aluminum foil; be sure it is sealed.
Place in a 300° to 325° oven.
Bake 3 to 4 hours.
Test with meat fork at 3 hours.
When tender, remove from oven, cool and place in refrigerator.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 - 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter, saute onions and add potatoes, carrots, water and salt.
Cook until tender.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons cornstarch or flour to 2 cups milk.
Mash potatoes and add milk.
Cook until thickened.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Combine the egg, sugar, molasses, hot water, soda, salt and spices.
Add the flour and cream of tartar.
Mix ingredients. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg, flour and extracts; mix well.
Make tiny balls and dip in sugar.
Flatten balls and put on baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: spinach rice salad
directions: Cook rice to package directions.
Transfer to bowl.
Cool slightly.
Combine dressing, soy sauce and sugar.
Stir into warm rice.
Cover and chill.
Fold in remaining ingredients before serving.
Looks pretty to line bowl with whole spinach leaves, if desired.

title: zucchini apple betty
directions: Crust:
Cut together until crumbly the flour, sugar, salt and margarine.
Pat 1/2 of the mixture into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan and bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: spiced stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes. Bake at 450° for 1 hour or until tender. Cool slightly. Cut a lengthwise strip from top of each potato. Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells. Set shells aside. Place potato pulp in a medium bowl. Add cream cheese and next 4 ingredients. Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy. Stir in raisins. Spoon mixture evenly into sweet potato shells. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Makes 4 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix flour, cocoa and salt.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes and spread Marshmallow Creme on top.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Place crackers as needed to line a 1 1/2-quart baking dish (shallow).
Cover with oysters and cover oysters with more crackers.
Mix broth and celery soup; spread over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until brown.

title: creamed cabbage casserole
directions: Cut
cabbage
fine.
Boil
in
salted water (1 teaspoon salt to	quart)	for
minutes.
Drain well.	Place 1/2 of cabbage in Pyrex dish; add layer of white sauce.
Add balance of cabbage and another layer of white sauce.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Cook 30 minutes at 300°.

title: white chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Add flour and salt.
Mix.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake 12 to 13 minutes, then roll in confectioners sugar.
Let cool before eating.
Enjoy!

title: baked cabbage
directions: In frying pan, cook the hamburg and onion until tender, then stir in spices.
In a square pan, 9 x 13-inch, layer the cabbage, then put some hamburg on top and another layer of cabbage on top. Pour in the can of tomato soup.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bavarian inn house dressing(from frakenmuth, michigan restaurant)
directions: Stir together dressing mix, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and dill weed.
Stir in mayonnaise, buttermilk, salad dressing and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix flour, butter, sugar, salt and paprika.
Add to corn.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Add to corn mixture; mix well.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown like a custard.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Pour into well-greased quart size casserole. Set casserole in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place berries in pie shell.
Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir and let set until almost lukewarm.
Put on berries.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: *I use 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Cut cherries in half.
Take about 1 teaspoon of mixture and put into palm of hand; flatten.
Put the 1/2 cherry in the middle.
Roll into a ball.
Freeze until hard. Melt chocolate.
Dip balls, then chill again.

title: unique green salad
directions: Toss with Poppy Seed Dressing.

title: tasty beef rice balls
directions: Mix together thoroughly beef, onion, rice crumbs, milk and seasonings.
Shape with hands into 1-inch balls.

title: pear helene
directions: Place pear half in dessert dish, rounded side down.
Fill hollow with ice cream.
Pour chocolate sauce over ice cream. Freeze.

title: casserole
directions: Brown hamburg; add chopped onion and green pepper.
Add to cooked meat the tomato sauce.
Set aside.
Mix together cottage cheese, cream cheese (softened) and sour cream.
Layer cooked noodles, cheese mix, then hamburg.
Cook at 375° for 3/4 hour. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer chicken until tender in well seasoned water.
Measure 1 quart broth back into pan.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Bone chicken; dice.
Add diced chicken and rest of ingredients to drained spaghetti.

title: favorite reuben
directions: Top 1 bread slice with cheese, turkey pastrami, sauerkraut, dressing and second bread slice.
Spread sandwich with margarine. Cook in skillet on medium heat until lightly browned on both sides.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: southern sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, vegetable oil, sugar, confectioners sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; blend into egg mixture.
Chill.
Roll teaspoon of dough into balls; roll in additional sugar.
Press down on lightly greased cookie sheet with fork or bottom of oiled glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
8 dozen cookies.

title: chicken in spanish rice
directions: Dredge cut up chicken in flour and brown quickly in hot shortening.
Remove
chicken and drain shortening.	Return 1/3 cup of	shortening
to	skillet
and
add
the vegetables, all except pimento,
into the skillet.
Cook until tender and stir now and then.
Add	the
dry
rice and pimento and cook 3 minutes.	Add cream
of
chicken	soup
and 1 can of water to the skillet contents
and
stir in the seasoning (salt, pepper and chili powder).
Pour
mixture
in
a large casserole and place the chicken on	top.
Cover
and
bake	1
1/2 hours in a 350° oven. I use electric skillet from beginning to finish.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together in a blender.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat with mixer until well mixed, 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into freezer can; add milk to full mark on cake.
Stir together and freeze.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Slice cucumbers, onions and peppers thinly. Mix with salt and bury in cracked ice. Let stand for 3 hours.

title: spaghetti squash
directions: Halve squash lengthwise; scoop out seeds.
Place cut side down in pan with 2 inches water.
Cover and boil 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a large saucepan, boil 4 to 6 cups of water. Add 1 tablespoon of oil and dash of salt.
Pour in macaroni and stir. Boil gently for 10 minutes or until done.

title: 24 hour omelet(this recipe serves 32; i cut in half for at home.)
directions: Butter one side of bread.
Cut bread in 1-inch cubes.
Place evenly in well-greased pan.
Sprinkle cheese over bread.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 hour or until mixture is set.
Uncover for last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: zoe's cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add vanilla.
Add egg and oil; sift dry ingredients (flour, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda).
Mix with creamy mixture.
Add Rice Krispies, walnuts, oatmeal and coconut.
If you omit the coconut, add 3/4 cup more Rice Krispies.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Roll chicken breasts in margarine and Parmesan cheese, then roll chicken in bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1-quart dish.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: muffins
directions: Melt the butter.
Stir in the sour cream.
Mix in the flour until moistened.
Do not overstir, or muffins will be tough.
Drop mixture into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: oatmeal fruit cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, white sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; then add oats and blend well.
Add raisins, dates, pecans and coconut; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° about 10 minutes.

title: turkey cranberry wreath
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll crescent dough; separate into 16 triangles.
With wide ends of triangles toward the center, arrange 8 triangles in a circle on large round stone.
Corners of wide ends will touch and points will extend 1-inch beyond edge of baking stone.
Match wide end of each remaining triangle to wide end of each outer triangle; seal seams using dough and pizza roller.
(Points will overlap in center, do not seal.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and then drain the water off.
Grate up all the cheese.
Mix in the soup, eggs and mayonnaise.
Put in rectangular baking pan and bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine zucchini, sugar, cinnamon, eggs, flour, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 425°
for 10 minutes and
for 15 minutes.
Use knife to test.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Combine milk and vinegar (or use buttermilk).
Cream shortening and sugar well together.
Add eggs and beat for one minute.
Sift together flour and salt.
Combine sour milk and vanilla.
Add alternately with dry ingredients, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Mix soda with cocoa and warm water. Add to batter and mix well.
Pour into two 8 or 9-inch pans that have been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time, flour, salt, vanilla and Hershey syrup.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: lazy cherry cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and milk.
Pour the batter over the melted butter.
Pour in the cherries with the juice.
Sprinkle with the extra cup of sugar, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: magic chocolate frosting
directions: In microwave bowl combine all ingredients except vanilla. Heat and stir until thickened.
Cool.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread on cooled cakes.
Makes 1 1/2 cups frosting or enough to frost top and sides of two 8-inch layer cakes or 12 cupcakes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Note:
Chicken soup is a cure all to good health.

title: mandarin almond muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 6 (3-inch) muffin pan cups.
In large bowl, combine both flours, sugars, almonds, baking powder, salt, allspice and nutmeg.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutter or roll into balls and press with fork.
May be decorated (before baking) with piece of candied cherry in center.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
May be decorated with frosting and candy sprinkles if desired.

title: oven cooked ham or turkey
directions: Put ham and water in a roaster, skin side up.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover roaster and place in oven.
Turn oven to 500° for 15 minutes.
Turn off and don't open oven door.
Leave for 3 hours; turn oven back to 500° and leave for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave for 6 to 8 hours (or longer).
Will do no harm if left overnight.

title: beef dip in crusty round
directions: Hollow out center of one bread round and cube the other bread round into 1-inch cubes.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, beef and all seasonings in a medium size bowl.
Pour dip into the hollowed bread round and serve with bread cubes for dipping.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine.
Spread cracker crumbs on bottom of dish; save some to garnish the top. Put boiled broccoli on top of crackers.

title: knox blocks
directions: Mix gelatine and jello thoroughly.
Add boiling water and stir for 1 minute.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into favorite shapes.
Red and green jello make a wonderful Christmas platter.
Will hold up for a couple of hours on table.

title: dump cake
directions: Put the following in a
9 x 13-inch greased pan in this order: fruit cocktail, cake mix and pineapple.
Mix around.
Cut up the oleo on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: ohio candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips. Stir in peanuts and chow mein noodles. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: chicken in a crock
directions: First clean and remove inner parts of chicken.
Place potatoes, carrots, onion and bell peppers in bottom of crock.
Then place whole chicken on top.
Add 1/4 cup of water.
Then salt, pepper, garlic salt, seasoning salt and 1 package Lipton soup on top.
Pour sliced mushrooms on top.
Cover and cook on high in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours.
You may also cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand overnight. Add 3 or 4 sliced bananas. Good!

title: layered hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion. Drain fat. Return to stove top and add tomato sauce. Simmer for 5 minutes. Add green beans to hamburger mixture and simmer for 10 minutes more.

title: ginger fruit dip
directions: Mix for 1 minute.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry cream cheese cake
directions: Cut angel food cake in half.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar together; put in middle of cake.
Put strawberries in middle.
Put top of cake on.
Add mixture to the top also plus strawberries.

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and deviled ham, mixing until well blended. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: egg lemon soup(low cholesterol)
directions: Heat chicken broth.
Add rice and cook until tender.
Remove from heat. Bring egg substitute to room temperature.
Beat lemon juice into egg substitute. Whisk half the broth, a little at a time, into egg substitute mixture.
Pour egg mixture back into remaining broth, mixing well. Return to low heat and cook, stirring constantly, just until soup is thickened. Do not boil.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk, alternating.
Mix well. Add flavorings and baking powder last.
Put in a large greased tube pan.
Line bottom of pan with 2 layers of paper.
Put in cold oven.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open oven door until time is up.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Put rolls over bottom of pan, flatten them out.
Crumble sausage over rolls.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper well; pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: holiday butterhorns
directions: Cream butter with cottage cheese, blend in salt and flour. Shape into a ball.
Divide dough into thirds.
Roll each piece into 12 inch round; brush with melted butter.
Combine cinnamon, brown sugar and walnuts.
Sprinkle 1/3 of nut mixture over each round.
Cut each into 16 wedges; start at wide edge, roll toward point.
Place point down on cookie sheet.
Brush with combined egg yolk and water. Bake at 375° about 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: *pecan nut roll
directions: Melt marshmallows and cherry juice over low heat.
Let cook. Mix cherries, pecans and crumbs into mix; spread and roll; place 1/2 cup of crumbs on wax paper, then spread mixture onto crumbs and roll up.
Slice with knife after cooling.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In mixing bowl, stir 2 cups sugar, flour and baking soda with a spoon to mix.
Add crushed pineapple, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Stir well with a spoon.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour and resift 3 times with baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Add shortening and cut in with pastry blender (2 knives or fork) until size of rice grains.
Add milk all at once and stir vigorously until stiff (the larger amount of milk may be needed in cold weather; dough should be stiff but soft).
Turn onto floured surface and knead from 12 to 15 times.
Roll or pat out 3/8 to 3/4-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter dipped in flour.
Put onto greased sheet; brush tops with butter (melted). Bake in oven at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix cooled hamburger, sour cream, soups, tomatoes and taco seasoning together. Grease a 9 x 13 baking dish or pan. Crush the chips and place 1/2 of the chips in the bottom of the dish. Pour the mix on top of the chips. Add the remaining chips, then put the grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In order given, spread each ingredient into pan.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
When cooled, cut in squares.
Yield:
20 to 24 servings.
Good!

title: yeast dough
directions: Mix together all except flour and yeast.
Add 2 cups flour; stir well.
Add yeast and stir.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Add remaining flour; mix well.
Knead 8 minutes.

title: prune pecan cookies
directions: In blender, puree egg and prunes until finely chopped.
Add sugar.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to prune mixture and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Top each cookie with a pecan half.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to wire racks to cool. Makes 2 dozen.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa to a rolling boil; let boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla, oats and nuts.
Beat until mixed. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake rolls as directed, only spread all over pan.
Let it cool. Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture on cooled crust. Top with broccoli, cauliflower, green peppers and fresh mushrooms.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Bake until meat is done, approximately 25 minutes, at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together as given.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in. Cook 45 minutes at 325°
until set.

title: chocolate covered banana pops
directions: Peel bananas and cut each into thirds.
Insert wooden stick into each banana piece.
Place on waxed paper covered tray.
Cover and freeze until firm.
In top of double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate chips and shortening.
You may also melt chocolate and shortening in microwave, stirring every 30 seconds until melted.
Remove bananas from freezer.
Dip each piece into chocolate and cover completely.
Allow excess to drip off.
Roll in peanuts.
Cover and return to freezer.
Serve frozen.

title: bacon corn bread
directions: Combine the flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add eggs, milk and cooking oil.
Beat just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Stir in bacon and turn mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 425° oven about 15 minutes; cool.
Cut into 1 1/4-inch squares.
To serve, spread each square with some cream cheese and a dollop of jelly.
Makes 54 squares.

title: strawberry cloud
directions: Wash and hull strawberries (resume a few for garnish).
Drain the tofu and blend it in a blender together with the strawberries, lemon juice and sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Add vanilla to taste and mix well.
Divide the mixture into 4 to 6 individual serving dishes and decorate with the reserved strawberries; chill.

title: curried fall-fruit compote
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat simmer onion in 2 Tbsp broth until limp. Add curry powder and cumin. Stir over medium-high heat about 15 seconds. Add remaining ingredients, including the brandy.
Cover and
cook over low heat 20 minutes until fruits are tender and flavors blended. Serve hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: darla's date cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Blend butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in dates and pecans.
Drop by half teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: boiled okra
directions: Cut and wash okra as desired.
Place salt pork in 1-quart container or pan.
Add 2 cups of water.
Add seasoning salt and bring to boil.
Add okra.
Turn temperature to low and add pepper. Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add butter.
Turn off heat, should simmer in its own liquid.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: adobo(chicken or pork)
directions: Cut chicken or pork into pieces.
Put in a saucepan and add vinegar, soy sauce, water, garlic, pepper and bay leaves.
Cover the saucepan and cook slowly until meat is tender and most of the broth has practically evaporated.
Serve hot with rice.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: With your hands, mix/knead the graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Remove 5 tablespoons of mixture and set aside.
In a greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan, gently, but firmly press crumb mixture in bottom of pan to form a base.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes, then remove from oven.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour remaining ingredients in large salad bowl.
Toss well, then garnish with Bac*O's.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown meat in shortening in a large frying pan.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top, then stir in; stir in water, parsley flakes, garlic powder, oregano and pepper.
Heat to boiling; cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Stir about 1/2 cup of the hot sauce into sour cream in a small bowl; stir back into mixture in frying pan.
Blend cornstarch with a little water until smooth in a cup; stir into mixture in pan.
Cook, stirring, until sauce thickens and boils 3 minutes.
Serve on noodles.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Fill with water.
Prepare and set overnight.

title: vegetarian nutmeat cutlets
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan; add mushrooms, walnuts and onion and stir until almost cooked.
Stir in seasoning and bread crumbs. Stir in eggs and mix well.
Let mixture get cold.
Shape mixture into cutlet shape or rounds.
Dip in flour, then egg, then flour and pan-fry until golden brown.

title: apple pie
directions: In a bowl, mix flour and sugar together.
Place a layer of apples in pie shell.
Add 1/2 of mixture of flour and sugar. Place another layer of apples; add remaining mixture.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate and unroll breadsticks.
Place 3 pepperoni slices in single layer over half of each breadstick. Fold remaining half over top; seal end and twist.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Combine next 2 ingredients in bowl and sprinkle over breadsticks.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with pizza sauce.

title: dinosaur tracks cupcakes
directions: Follow instructions on cake mix to make cupcakes.
Have a child put a few drops of food coloring in the frosting and mix thoroughly.
If using the coconut, add food coloring and mix thoroughly.
Have each child frost his/her own cupcake.
Place a small mint on the cupcake, somewhat centered, then place 3 Junior Mints or chocolate chips around one side of the small patty for claw marks.

title: watergate pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with the crushed pineapple with its juice. Fold in marshmallows and whipped topping.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve in a pretty bowl and garnish with well drained maraschino cherries.

title: angel food cake pudding
directions: Tear up cake in large bowl.
Prepare vanilla pudding as directed on box and pour over cake.
Add pineapple, nuts and cool whip.
Mix well.
Chill several hours.

title: homemade potato soup(crock pot)
directions: Put all ingredients except chives into crock pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8-10 hours.
Ladle soup into bowls and garnish with a sprinkle of chopped chives.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix and form small patties. Fry until golden brown.

title: nacho stuff
directions: Mix all together but the cheese.
Top with the cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: congealed cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and let cool completely.
Beat in sour cream with beater.
Add other ingredients; pour into mold and let congeal.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish.
Cover. Bake at 350° until warmed through, approximately 45 minutes.

title: fruit and bran muffins(makes 18 muffins)
directions: In a large bowl, combine the bran cereal with water; stir to moisten evenly, then allow to cool until lukewarm.
Add the egg, buttermilk, honey, butter, dried fruit and nuts.
Stir until well blended.

title: cheddar cheese cabbage
directions: Wash and cut cabbage into 6 wedges.
Heat 1-inch water in large pot.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Add cabbage.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes until crisp-tender.
Stir together soup, mustard and celery seed in saucepan.
Heat through.
Drain cabbage and remove to platter.
Pour soup mixture over wedges.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: english trifle
directions: Cut cake into small cubes; layer in the bottom of a dessert glass.
Continue to layer them alternately with pudding and raspberries, ending with a pudding layer.
Top with whipped cream. Sprinkle with almonds; garnish with a raspberry and mint leaf.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine sausage and cheese in bowl; blend well

with hands. Add baking mix; blend well. Roll mixture into marble-sized balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 30 minutes or until sausage is no longer pink. Serve hot or at room temperature. (Makes 60 sausage balls.)

title: mom's iranian chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, onion, potatoes, eggs, carrots and peas.
Add pickle chips, mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.

title: dijon pecan salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Line jelly roll pan with parchment paper or brush lightly with a little oil to prevent salmon from sticking to pan. Rinse and pat dry the salmon filets and place on sheet. Season with salt and pepper.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all but bacon in oven proof dish.
Place bacon on top. Cook at 350 for approx. 30-45 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, tomato sauce, eggs and salt.
Mix just until ingredients are blended.
In a shallow baking pan, shape meat mixture into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf.
Bake until meat loaf is cooked through, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese if desired and bake 5 minutes longer.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 portions.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin, add sherbet.
When partially set, add other ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: mock tuna salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, parsley, onions, lemon juice, soy sauce, salt and sesame seed.
Blend well and set aside.
Combine lettuce, chicken-like meat and celery; refrigerate.
Just before serving, combine the two mixtures with crisp noodles and toss gently.
To toast sesame seed, I put them in a heavy skillet over low heat and stir until toasted to a straw color.

title: million dollar dessert
directions: Mix cookies and butter and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool some.

title: warm fruit
directions: Place ingredients in large dish, putting pie filling last. Top with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate coconut dessert
directions: Boil chocolate chips and milk for 4 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted. Chill.

title: calypso sauce(a great dipping sauce for chicken wings)
directions: In a small saucepan, combine brown sugar with remaining ingredients.
Cok over medium heat, stirring until the sugar dissolves.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: hollandaise sauce for asparagus(cook some asparagus, then pour on this sauce.)
directions: In a bowl, cream the butter.
Add yolks, one at a time, and beat well.
Add lemon juice and seasonings.
Stir in hot water five minutes before serving, stirring rapidly.

title: carney's picnic chicken
directions: Individual servings to take on picnic.
Need section of aluminum foil (grease).
Put rice in center.
Pat butter on top. Add onion soup mix right from package on top of rice.
Add uncooked chicken and onion soup.
Roll up.
Put servings on baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Will keep warm for picnic.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine popcorn and nuts in lightly greased 14 x 11-inch roasting pan.
Mix well and set aside.
Melt margarine over low heat in medium saucepan. Add brown sugar and honey.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Add vanilla, stirring well.
Pour syrup over popcorn mixture, stirring until popcorn is evenly coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely and break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers.
Yields about 4 quarts.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and finely chop other vegetables.
Combine in bowl and add other ingredients.
Let stand for an hour.
When ready to serve, stir well.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Beat with mixer until smooth, about 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Bake in hot oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: crispy caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, Karo, oleo and salt for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Pour onto cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: cheesecake cupcakes with blueberries
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Line 12 mini muffin cups with foil cupcake liners. Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner. Trim cookie to fit if necessary. Beat together cream cheese and sugar on medium speed in large bowl until smooth. Add eggs, beating just until blended. Beat in sour cream, vanilla and lemon rind. On low speed, beat in flour. Stir in blueberries. Spoon batter into cups, dividing equally. Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until cakes are set. Cool cakes in pan on rack 20 minutes. Remove cakes to rack to cool further.

title: white chili
directions: Cook chicken in Dutch oven or stock pot until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts and chili is hot. Serve with corn chips or Tostados.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs and flour.
Add whipping cream last.
Put in cold oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fettucine with smoked salmon
directions: Combine cream and butter
in
medium saucepan.
Cook on medium high heat until thick, glossy and reduced by half.
Add salmon, chives and pepper.
Cook, stirring gently, one minute. Place cooked fettucine on serving platter and pour sauce over. Toss gently.
Sprinkle
with
parsley
and
serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
This makes a great first course.

title: sweets for the sweet, white valentine cookie
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and blend.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/16-inch thick on floured board.
Cut out with heart shaped cookie cutter, cutting 2 alike for each cookie. Place the bottom pieces on lightly greased baking sheet.
Spread a rounded teaspoonful of filling on each.
Cover with top cookie. Press edges together with floured fork or fingertips.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until browned.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: hurry up cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Add butter, egg, milk, salt, baking powder, vanilla, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, dust cake with confectioners sugar.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops; place in casserole, pour rice over pork chops.
Add soup plus water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover; cook in 350° oven 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet pasta(romania)
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water until done. Drain well. Heat maple syrup and walnuts/poppy seeds in a large pot over medium heat for 2-3 minutes. Add lemon rind, raisins, clove powder, and cinnamon. Cook for 3 more minutes. Now add cooked pasta. Mix well and serve warm. You can also pour into baking dish and bake at 350F for 20 minutes before serving. Serves 8.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add soups, oregano, noodles, mushrooms and pepperoni and mix together.
Put Mozzarella on top.
Bake until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: sandy k's potato cake
directions: Mix together lard, sugar, mashed potatoes and egg yolks.
Add cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and vanilla.
Stir well and add milk and self-rising flour.
Set aside.

title: caramel chews
directions: Melt butter and add sugar, corn syrup and sweetened condensed milk and stir continually until it boils and candy thermometer reads 240°. Remove from heat and add the nuts and vanilla. Lightly butter a pan and pour batter into pan. Leave at room temperature 3 or 4 hours until it hardens. Wrap in wax paper. Twist ends of paper and clip ends with scissors.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Place a slice of ham and cheese on chicken.
Roll up.
Brown floured chicken in oil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: do-not-peek chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly over a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Mix the mushrooms and celery soups together in a small bowl.
In a separate dish, combine melted margarine and water.
Pour over rice, and then spoon soup mixture over rice.
Lay chicken pieces on rice and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Do not peek during baking!

title: tangy hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, 1 cup cheese, chilies, sandwich spread, olives, onion, salt and pepper; mix lightly.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with combined remaining cheese and chips; continue baking until cheese is melted.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Mix carrots and raisins.
Add salt and salad dressing.
Mix lemon juice and sugar until well blended.
Stir into carrot mixture.
Chill.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Stir ham and bread crumbs together in ham grease and stuff in hollowed tomatoes.
Put plain bread crumbs on top.
Brown in oven and heat until tomatoes get soft.
The amounts of ingredients are estimated to how many tomatoes and size you use.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Bake
8 or 9-inch pie shell.
Spread 4 teaspoons peanut butter on baked pie shell.
Mix 2 boxes instant Jell-O pudding mix with 3 cups milk.
Pour over pie shell with peanut butter on it.
Top with Cool Whip and chill for 2 hours.

title: yogurt pancakes(light and fluffy)
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk, yogurt, vanilla, egg and oil.
Stir until mixed.
Do not overstir; batter will be lumpy.
Add blueberries, if desired.
Serves 2 to 4 people (I triple the recipe for my family).

title: squash pickles
directions: Let squash, onion and pepper set in salt and water 1 hour, then drain.
Mix the sugar, vinegar and celery and mustard seeds. Bring to a boil.
Pour over squash mixture and let boil 3 minutes.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: delores' green rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Let it stand.
Fold in Cheez Whiz.
Add well drained, cooked broccoli.
Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Add soup to celery and onion.

title: cocoa and cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except cola and marshmallows.
Blend at low speed; beat one minute at medium speed.
Add 1 cup cola; blend well, by hand.
Stir in miniature marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool and frost with Cola Icing.

title: dough ornaments
directions: Knead together. Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Don't forget to make a hole for hanging. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Decorate with acrylics or markers.

title: tropical pork chops
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 8 ingredients. Cover and simmer until sugar is dissolved, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat; set aside. Season pork chops with salt and pepper. In a skillet, cook pork, onion and garlic in oil until meat is browned. Add water and reserved sauce. Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 20 to 25 minutes or until the meat is no longer pink, adding more water if needed. Stir in pineapple and heat through. Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes.
Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: punch
directions: Water and juices can be mixed a couple of days ahead.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale. Put sherbet in ball or blend into punch.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, raisins, bacon, onion, cheese, and almonds together.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar together and toss with salad.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Just before removing from oven, top with miniature marshmallows and brown.

title: casserole party potatoes
directions: Cook peeled

potatoes in small amount of boiling water until tender, then drain. Beat cream cheese with sour cream. Add hot potatoes gradually, beating until light and fluffy. Add more sour cream, if necessary. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Spoon potatoes into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Brush with softened butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Warm in 300° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth in top of a double boiler.
Dip caramel patties into chocolate and place on wax paper until cool.

title: egg brunch
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain and cut into slices.
Place bread cubes into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Place sausage on top of cheese.
Beat eggs, 2 1/4 cups milk and dry mustard together.
Pour over the bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, dilute soup with 2 tablespoons milk and pour over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Beat until it gets thick.
Spread on top of second layer.
Top with large Cool Whip.
Grate one Hershey bar on top or sprinkle nuts on top.

title: chicken flamingo
directions: Saute chicken breast in butter or oil until golden brown. Place chicken in baking dish.
Put cheese on top of chicken.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Keep hot.
Meanwhile, put stock, wine, garlic, broccoli, mushrooms, ham and peppers in a skillet. Bring to a boil and thicken by adding butter rolled in flour. Serve over hot chicken.
Serves 1.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until forms soft ball in cold water when tested.
Let cool in sink of cold water.
Beat all the time pan is in water.
When thick enough, pour on buttered platter.

title: red, white and blue dessert
directions: In large mixing bowl beat cream cheese, sugar and extracts. Fold in whipped cream.
Place 1/3 mixture in 4-quart bowl. Reserve 20 strawberry halves and 1/2 cup blueberries for garnish. Layer 1/2 of remaining berries over cream mixture.
Top with another 1/3 of cream mixture and remaining berries.
Spread the remaining cream mixture on top.
Use the reserved strawberries and blueberries to make a flag design on top.
(For example: a field of blue with 4 red stripes.)
Yield:
18 servings.

title: kentucky fried chicken slaw
directions: Mix
together sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and mayonnaise. Bring to a hard boil.
Boil 1 minute. Pour boiled mixture over grated cabbage, onion and carrot.	Let stand.

title: lemon-lime fizz
directions: Fill blender 1/2 full with crushed ice.
Add lemon-lime.
Use concentrate can to measure 1/3 can half and half and add to blender.
Fill blender with wine; blend and serve.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Add cream of tartar. Gradually add sugar into which the cornstarch has been mixed. Beat until stiff and shiny.
Pile on pie.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350° or until light brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and mash.
Melt butter or margarine in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix squash with all ingredients but cinnamon.
Mix well, pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: First Day:
Combine ingredients in a measuring cup.
Brush over both sides of brisket.
Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken, reserving about 10 ounces of broth from chicken.
Heat all soups and broth until
hot (slow boil). Add chicken and rice.
Put into greased casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together, cook at 350° for 30-45 minutes until brown.

title: mother's lemon jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix and lemon Jell-O together.
Add oil, water, eggs (one at a time) and lemon extract.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven while cooking.

title: chickamauga chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Sift flour and beat into creamed mixture.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add oats, Rice Krispies, coconut, pecans and butterscotch chips; mix well.
Add vanilla and stir.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes.
Bake less for chewy cookies and more for crisp cookies.
Yield:
100 cookies.

title: pumpkin squares(makes one 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy. Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda. Spread in pan (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: red hot jello salad
directions: Melt red hots in boiling water.
Pour over Jell-O.
Add applesauce.
Butter jello mold before pouring in Jell-O.
Chill.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
It may be poured over chicken or pork pieces.

title: brunswick stew
directions: In 2 quart casserole, fry bacon until crisp and remove. Brown chicken
in
bacon	fat
and remove.
In same casserole, brown onion, garlic, celery and carrots.	Add chicken, 1 quart water and seasonings.
Cover
and
simmer over low heat for 1 hour.	Remove chicken
pieces.
Shred meat from bones and set aside.
To
the broth,
add tomato, corn, beans and potatoes. Cover and
simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Add chicken and
cook
for 15 minutes.
Before serving, add sherry or Madeira.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peaceable fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy, 2-quart saucepan. Add first 5 ingredients and stir well over low heat until melted.

Bring to a boil over medium heat; reduce to low heat and cook without stirring until mixture reaches soft-boil stage (235° on candy thermometer). Remove pan from heat and let stand until lukewarm. Stir in remaining ingredients and beat vigorously until mixture just begins to lose its gloss and mounds when dropped from spoon. Pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan. When cool, cut into squares. Yield: about 1 pound.

title: louisiana shrimp
directions: Combine peppers and herbs in a bowl.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add spices, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside 30 minutes.
Return the skillet to medium-high heat until bubbly. Add the shrimp and cook until the shells turn pink, turning once. Place the pan under the broiler and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Place shrimp in bowl and pour sauce over shrimp.
Serve with French bread and cooked rice.
Serves 2 to 3 as main dish, 4 to 6 as appetizer.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dry mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Place 1/2 of crumbled corn bread in bottom of large serving bowl.
Top with 1/2 of beans, tomatoes, peppers, onions, cheese, bacon, corn and Hidden Valley dry mixture.
Repeat with remaining ingredients. Save enough cheese and bacon to sprinkle on top.
Cover and chill. Serves 10 to 12.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook flour, milk, sugar and egg until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and mix well.
Slice bananas and layer in 9 x 9-inch pan the pudding and bananas.
Sprinkle nuts over top. Refrigerate.

title: cheese tidbits
directions: Toast Rice Krispies in oven at 250° for 3 minutes; set aside. Mix first 5 ingredients, then add Rice Krispies.
Make quarter-size balls, then flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Spread potatoes in dish.
Melt butter and drizzle over potatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over potatoes.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with more cheese 15 minutes before removing from oven.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix potatoes with soup, sour cream, onion and melted oleo.
Add 1 cup cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Reserve remaining 1/4 cup cheese as garnish.
Pour mixture into a well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with reserved cheese if desired.
Can top with crushed corn flakes.
Makes 8 servings each with 243 calories, 14 g. fat and 33 mg.
cholesterol.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Mix together flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Peel and slice 4 peaches.
Lay in rows on top of batter.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over peaches.
Pour water over all.
Bake at 350° approximately 50 minutes.
Good served warm with milk.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crusts away.
Butter bread.
Cook sausage, scrambled. Drain.
Place 6 slices of bread in 3-quart casserole dish. Spread half of sausage and cheese over bread.
Repeat bread, sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over mixture. Press down to soak.
Refrigerate overnight, uncovered.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 plus.

title: no mess lasagna
directions: Spread 3/4 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place uncooked noodles on sauce, add layer of hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup cottage cheese mixture on noodles, then a layer of Mozzarella cheese on top of that.
Then top with sauce. Repeat layers about 3 times.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over the top of lasagna.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk to soft ball stage (234°-240°). Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, marshmallow fluff and vanilla. Stir until the candy loses its gloss. Pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Pour liquid margarine into saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir until blended.
Slowly add milk, stirring to keep smooth.
Cook until thick and starts to come to a boil.
Slice potatoes thinly.

title: simple fish chowder
directions: Fry
bacon
in heavy pot until brown.
Add potatoes and onions.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, V-8 juice and fish. Let simmer for about 1 hour.

title: party punch
directions: Place jello in boiling water.
(Use strawberry for red punch or lime for green.)
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Cool. Add cold water, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
At this point, you can refrigerate or freeze until needed.
Partially thaw, place in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and top with sherbet.
Stir slowly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Save 1 1/2 cups water.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix broccoli, rice, onion and water.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Top mixture with 2 tablespoons melted margarine and 3/4 cup corn flake crumbs.
Bake in greased 9 x 12-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: easy baked doves
directions: Season doves to taste with salt, pepper and thyme.
Place in casserole dish and pour soup and water over top.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Tie spices in cheesecloth.
Add to cider, salt and sugar.
Add sliced lemon.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove spices and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together until smooth.
Pour into chocolate wafer crust.
Chill.
May be garnished with chocolate.

title: great grandmother's snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix the margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly. Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Stir in with margarine
mixture. Shape dough in 1-inch balls. Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Put onto ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin-apple muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add to the flour and sugar mix, then add the apples; spoon into greased or lined muffin cups. Sprinkle Streusel Topping over muffins.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Put in bowl and stir until batter is moist (lump, don't smooth).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, eggs and almond extract in a bowl.
Add cherry pie filling and stir until just moistened.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry frosty
directions: Whirl in blender.
Makes 1 pint.
This is a high nutrient breakfast with a slice of wheat toast.

title: old fashioned popcorn balls
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Mix well and pour over popped corn.	Makes 12 balls.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package. Mix together the next 5 ingredients. Saute onions in butter in microwave.
Mix onions and broccoli with other ingredients. Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Combine bacon and onion in 8-inch round dish.
Cook at High for 3 to 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Stir in flour, vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Cook at High for 1 to 3 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Add potatoes.
Cook at High for 4 to 5 minutes; stir occasionally. Serve warm.

title: prune fluff
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and whisk until light and fluffy.
Serve well chilled.
Mother Nature helper.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger.
Add celery and onion.
Simmer and do not drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms and simmer.
Add oregano and garlic to taste.
Delicious!

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet over medium heat until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Discard drippings. Meanwhile, sprinkle slices evenly on both sides with sugar, salt and pepper.
Place flour and egg separately in 2 shallow dishes. Dip tomatoes in flour to coat, shaking off excess.
Dip in egg, turning to coat completely.
Then dip in flour again.
Add butter or margarine to same skillet and melt over medium heat.
Add tomato slices and cook until golden (about 3 minutes) per side. Serve with bacon.
Yields 4 servings.

title: the famous valley grandma penz cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix ingredients together.
Shape cheese into a ball using wax paper.
Leave wax paper wrapped around cheese and place in freezer.
Take cheese ball out 30 to 45 minutes before serving.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cook spaghetti 10 minutes and drain.
Spread spaghetti in the casserole dish and cover with tomato sauce.
Spread on 1/2 of Swiss cheese, 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese, all the mushrooms and onion.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Add remaining ingredients in the same order, finishing with pepperoni. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until bubbly.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Coat graham cracker crusts with beaten egg yolk.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 5 minutes; cool.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice; mix well.
Add well drained pineapple, whipped topping, walnuts and all but 16 cherry halves.
Mix well.
Divide mixture between prepared crusts. Refrigerate overnight.
Decorate each with 8 cherry halves before serving.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until done. Save broth and cook noodles in it. Saute onion in margarine. Add flour.
Mix everything else together well and put in a large 8 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Cream sugar to butter.
Add vanilla; beat eggs and add to butter mixture.
Add flour to mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts; pour into frozen pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: layer salad
directions: Add in layers to a large, glass bowl.
Chill to serve.
Can add egg yolks and pepper.

title: dakota beans
directions: Drain and rinse kidney beans and butter beans.
Brown hamburger and onions until cooked. Drain off excess grease.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in roaster or large casserole. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes in a jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 12 1/2-inches.
Cool and ice.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Brown meat and onions in oil. Add water.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°. Pour meat mixture into ungreased baking dish, 9 x 13-inches. Arrange potatoes on meat.
Mix together soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cereal.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.

title: margarita punch
directions: *Crystal Lite comes in a 1.8 ounce container, which contains 4 tubs inside.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box and let cool.

title: soda pop cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in oblong pan.
Cool.
Take a fork and make holes in cake.
Mix jello with boiling water.
Add soda pop. Pour over cake.
Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and pour over stuffing.
Mash squash in bowl and add all other ingredients.
Line 1/2 of the stuffing into the casserole dish.
Add squash mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade fries
directions: Drop a few potatoes into boiling water after water starts to boil again, boil 2 minutes.
Lift out and drain on paper towel. Spread out on sprayed cookie sheet.
Freeze.
Do all potatoes as same.
After frozen, solid pack in Ziploc bags to store in freezer until needed.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box and spoon over nuts and coconut mixture.
