In saucepan, mix until melted oleo, cream cheese and sugar.
Spoon all over cake.
Bake this at 325° or 350° until done.
Test with toothpick.
This takes about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 3 cake pans.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon, then mix with apples. Place in the pie shell.
Sift remaining sugar and flour in a bowl. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumbs over pie.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake for about 45 minutes longer.

title: cran-raspberry float(flavorful beverage)
directions: Fill each of 4 tall glasses with spoonfuls of raspberry sherbet.
Pour 3/4 cup cranberry juice cocktail into each glass. Carefully fill with lemon-lime carbonated beverage; stir gently. Garnish with mint sprigs or fresh or frozen raspberries, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raspberry tapioca salad
directions: Boil water, add tapioca and stir for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and Jell-O.

title: delicious dirt
directions: Crush Oreos in blender.
Spread 1 cup of Oreos in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: halva(spiced wheat-almond pudding)
directions: Stir sugar into water, stirring until sugar dissolves. Continue boiling over medium heat until sugar melts completely.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Prepare fresh coconut and chop or shred in food processor. Mix with remaining ingredients, saving some red and green cherries whole and nut halves to decorate top of cake.
Press tightly into loaf pans, a tube pan or ring pans.
Refrigerate at least 3 to 5 days before serving.

title: million dollar pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice; fold in pineapple, cherries, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into pie crusts. Refrigerate until set.

title: french onion soup
directions: In bottom of Dutch oven, brown onions in 2 tablespoons of melted margarine until tender.
Add stock; bring to a boil and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in individual ovenproof bowls. In oven, brown bread chunks tossed in remaining 6 tablespoons of melted margarine and Parmesan cheese.
Place toasted bread and Mozzarella on top of bowls of soup.
Place under broiler to brown. Serve immediately.

title: macaroni cheese casserole(makes 6 servings)
directions: Chicken breasts must be boiled done. Chicken breasts also must be chopped up. Cook for 30 minutes in oven or 1 hour longer.

title: strawberry shakes
directions: Put strawberries and their juice into blender container with adult help.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Scoop some of the ice cream or yogurt into 3 tall glasses.
Put the rest of the ice cream of yogurt into the blender container.
With adult help, cover and blend until smooth.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Add nuts.
Shape into rolls (finger-size).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 45 minutes.
Slightly cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix and make dough. Roll out very very thin or dumplings will be tough. Cut in strips 1-inch wide. Lay on cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Freeze.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter in a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and salt.
Pour over popped corn.
Mix well.
Place in large roaster pan and place in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir after 30 minutes.
Pour out on wax paper to cool. Cool well.
Store in airtight container.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Put into a big bowl and mix margarine, sugar and egg.
Put into another bowl flour, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar. Add flour mixture to first bowl.
Mix well.
Dough should be soft and easy to handle.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour if dough is too sticky.
Combine in a small dish and set aside sugar-cinnamon combination.
Roll dough into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Cookies should be soft and puffy.
Cool on rack.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Chop into bite size pieces.
Chop onion.
Put chicken, onion, chili peppers and drained mushrooms in large saucepan.
Add spices, salt and pepper to taste.
Add about 1/2 container sour cream.
Heat to mix flavors.
Mix in chicken broth.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add beaten egg and applesauce. Mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add raisins, nuts and vanilla. Bake in a jelly roll pan for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix together and spread on top.
Sprinkle 4 ounces of grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours.

title: cafe swiss mocha
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1 level tablespoon of mix with 6 ounces boiling water for each cup. Makes 14 servings.

title: almond-turkey bake
directions: Fit pastry into 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Toss cheese with flour to coat.
Combine 3/4 cup cheese with 1/2 cup almonds; add remaining ingredients.
Fill pie crust and top with remaining cheese and almonds.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Great for leftover Thanksgiving turkey!

title: cheese grits
directions: Prepare grits as you usually do for your family.
Put in a small baking dish with grated onion and Velveeta cheese to taste. Bake at 425° until bubbly hot and serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together the potatoes, butter, sugar, salt, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour into casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix until crumbly.
Stir in pecans.
Spread on top of sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southwestern beans
directions: Cover; simmer beans for 3 to 3 1/2 hours, until tender.
In large skillet, cook bacon, onions and garlic until bacon is crisp. Add bacon mixture and rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Simmer, uncovered, an additional 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: easy, delicious dessert
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Then beat in sugar, baking powder and vanilla.
Fold in crushed crackers and the nuts. Spread in ungreased 9-inch pie tin.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°; cool.
Spread with sweetened whipped cream and sprinkle with grated chocolate.

title: rosie's wontons
directions: Combine all ingredients (except wrappers) in blender and make a paste.
Put scant teaspoon in wonton wrapper.
Fold in half, wetting two edges and folding together.
Will make good seal.
Fry until brown in Fry Daddy.

title: olive nut sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let stand overnight. Delicious!!!

title: sorghum cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased sheets about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown flour and shortening in large pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook an hour or longer, if preferred.
Add okra, if desired.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar until fluffy and smooth.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Chill dough for 1 1/2 hours.
Roll out dough to cut out.
Bake cookies at 375° on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water until thick.
Mash cranberry sauce until soft and mix with jello.
Add oranges, pineapple and nuts. Place in mold and chill until firm.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and dice onion and green pepper. Mix together. Add mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, basil, coriander, celery seed, salt and pepper to taste. Eat.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Combine minced chicken with bread crumbs, eggs, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into balls or logs.
Dip into beaten eggs and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry light brown in hot oil and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions, pepper and ham.
Mix cheese, Accent and other ingredients all together and roll into a ball.
Then roll in crushed nuts to cover.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 2 1/2 minutes.
Start counting time when sugar mix reaches a full boil.
Remove from heat, add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Drop a spoonful onto wax paper.

title: grandma's beef stew
directions: Cut meat in 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Peel vegetables.
Cut into chunks or wedges.
Brown meat in butter in heavy Dutch oven. Remove and reserve.
Saute vegetables in same pan a few minutes until lightly browned.
Add meat and chopped parsley to vegetables.
Stir in spices and broth.
Add vinegar.
Cover and simmer for 1 3/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Add sprouts and peas.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Garnish with red pepper, if used.

title: chili relleno pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute green pepper and onion. Combine beef, spices, onion, pepper and cheeses.
Place chilies in bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Place beef and cheese mixture on top of chilies.
Combine eggs, half and half and flour; beat well.
Pour over beef and cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over all and bake 10 minutes longer. Cut into squares to serve.
Equally as good without the ground beef.
Makes 9 servings.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Scald milk. Stir in sugar, salt and margarine. Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm water in large bowl. Sprinkle in yeast, then stir until dissolved. Add lukewarm milk mixture, starter and 2 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth. Stir in additional flour to make stiff dough. Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes). Place in greased bowl; turn once to grease top. Cover. Let rise in warm place until doubled. Punch down. Divide in 3 parts. Form each part into smooth round ball or roll out and cut. Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add soda to sour cream and add alternately with flour to mixture.
Add salt, vanilla and whiskey.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Insert toothpick in center to test for doneness.

title: tea punch
directions: Pour tea over sugar and as soon as sugar is dissolved, add fruit juices.
Strain into punch bowl over a large piece of ice. Just before serving, add ginger ale, charged water and slices of orange.
For tea infusion, add 2 teaspoons tea and 1 cup boiling water.
Serves 12.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo.
Add Crisco; cream.
Add eggs; beat. Add flour; blend well.
Add nuts, chips and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until firm around side of pan, but soft in center and golden brown.
Use a 9 x 13-inch or similar pan.

title: low-cal banana split
directions: Make graham cracker crust in 9 x 13-inch pan with 6 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix Milnot and 3 cups sugar in large kettle.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil slowly until mixture forms soft ball when dropped into a glass of cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter or margarine and peanut butter.
When well mixed, continue to stir to help cool.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Let cool; cut into squares and serve.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes and cool.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each egg.
Blend in flour slowly.
Add vanilla and beat until well blended.
Grease 3 mini-loaf pans and flour the pans.
Shake off excess flour.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (until toothpick comes out clean).
Cool before removing from the pan.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients on slow speed in mixer until well blended and uniform.
Add the buttermilk and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until set and brown on top.

title: coleslaw
directions: Crisp the cabbage in ice water if necessary; drain thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to combine.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp lo mein
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok.
Add shrimp; cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp are firm and pink.
Remove shrimp from skillet.
Add chicken broth, soy sauce, sugar, ginger and garlic powder to skillet.
Bring to boil.
Add egg noodles, onion and frozen vegetables; return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until egg noodles and vegetables are tender.
Stir in shrimp.
In small bowl, stir cornstarch into water until dissolved.
Gradually stir into mixture in skillet.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until sauce is bubbly and thickened.
Makes 5 servings.

title: baked peach butter
directions: Place sliced peaches and water in an 8-quart stainless steel or enamel pot and cook over medium heat until peaches are soft, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir frequently to prevent peaches from sticking.
When fruit is tender, add lemon juice and honey and stir to combine.
Put the peach mixture through a food mill, blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Pour and divide the puree into two shallow 9 x 13-inch baking pans.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.
Continue baking, stirring every 15 or 20 minutes, until the butter is thick.
This will take approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
The peach butter will be thick, fine textured and a rich reddish-amber color.

title: orange walnuts
directions: Combine sugar and juice in 2-quart pan.
Cook to soft ball stage (240°).
Remove from heat; add peel, vanilla and walnuts. Stir until syrup begins to look cloudy.
Before it hardens, spread mix on waxed paper-lined cookie sheets so nuts don't overlap. When cool, break up.
Store covered in fridge or freezer.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: pepper relish
directions: Halve, seed and chop peppers (9 cups).
Layer with salt in a large glass bowl.
Allow to stand at room temperature, stirring several times for 3 hours.
Drain peppers well to remove all liquid.
Combine drained peppers, tomatoes and onions in a large kettle; stir in sugar and vinegar.
Tie mixed pickling spices in cheesecloth and crack with a hammer.
Add to kettle.
Bring to boiling, stirring often.
Lower heat; simmer, stirring frequently near the end of cooking time to prevent scorching, 30 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Remove spice bag.
Ladle into 8 hot, sterilized, 8 ounce jars; seal and cool.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Slice beef very thinly across the grain into bite size strips; set aside.
Combine the broth, soy sauce and sugar; set aside.
Preheat a wok or a 10-inch skillet over high heat; add oil.
Add the beef to hot wok; stir-fry 2 minutes or until meat is just browned.
Add Chinese cabbage, onions, shirataki, if desired, mushrooms and bamboo shoots.
Stir the soy mixture; stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in the spinach and tofu.
Cover and cook for 1 to 2 minutes or just until ingredients are heated through and spinach is wilted.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir until melted.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil 6 large potatoes with peels intact.
Peel potatoes; chill thoroughly.
Grate.
Melt 1 stick margarine and toss with potatoes.
Add cheese, sour cream, green onion and salt.
Marinate at least 6 hours.
Bake 1/2 hour at 300°.
Serves 12.
Freezes well.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and cut into cubes.
Mix with the other ingredients.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Grease pan and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef, celery and onion.
When browned, mix in rest of ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: speedy quiche
directions: Saute Spam, onion and green pepper in oil until vegetables are
tender.
Spoon
lightly in greased 10-inch deep pie dish
or 8
x
12-inch
cake pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender or mixer until smooth.
Bake at 400°
about 30
to
minutes or until set.	Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: refrigerator white rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup of flour.
Beat well. Beat in yeast mixture and egg.
Add remaining flour.
Mix well. Place in greased bowl.
Grease surface.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: yogurt soup
directions: Place water, lamb, onions, split peas, spinach, scallions, salt and pepper in saucepan; bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Stir in the rice and cook over moderate heat for about 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the yogurt; stir one minute without boiling and remove from the heat.
Heat the oil in a frying pan, add the mint and stir for one minute.
Add to the soup and serve.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine until fluffy.
Add sugar, beating well.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture; beat on low until well blended.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Break into small pieces.
Stir sausage, cheese and eggs together.
Pour over bread in baking dish.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: robin's fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon, place in bowl. Drain most of bacon fat from pan, fry cabbage in frying pan until it starts to turn tender.
Can add a little water if needed.
Crumble bacon on top and serve.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Add egg yolks, juice
and
rind
to
beaten milk.
Pour this over bottom layer of
crumbs.
Top this with a thin layer of whipped cream.
Cover with remaining crumbs and chill.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add shortening.
Mix and beat well the eggs with the vanilla and milk.
Mix dough like for pie crust.
Add egg mixture.
Roll and cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (10 to 15 minutes).
Frost and decorate.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put all ingredients, except nuts, in microwave-safe bowl, with margarine on top.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes on High, stirring halfway through cycle.
Stir in nuts and pour into greased dish or pan.
Cut into pieces when cool.

title: salmon spread
directions: Drain and rinse salmon.
Mix all ingredients together well and refrigerate to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers.

title: southwestern barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Use on beef, pork or chicken.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: If apples lack tartness, sprinkle with about 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Mix with apples.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: chunky chicken bites
directions: Put whole crackers, sage and paprika in a plastic bag; close bag and crush crackers.
In a small bowl, dip chicken pieces into milk.
Put chicken pieces in bag with crumbs; close bag and shake to coat chicken.
Place chicken on baking sheet and bake at 450° for 6 to 8 minutes or microwave for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve hot with ketchup or barbecue sauce.

title: baked oysters italiano
directions: Drain oysters.
Combine butter, olive oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, wine and garlic.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and parsley.

title: grandma's famous spiced coffee cake
directions: Pour into 2 small pans.
Sprinkle with topping and bake.

title: vegetable cheddar chowder
directions: Combine water and bouillon cubes in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir cheese sauce, pimiento and hot sauce into vegetable mixture.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated; do not boil.
Garnish each serving with pimiento cutouts and a parsley sprig.

title: granny's hamburger vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer covered 15 minutes or until noodles and vegetables are tender.

title: apple nut dessert
directions: Beat egg. Add sugar and vanilla. Separately mix flour, baking powder and salt. Add flour mixture to egg mixture. Stir in apples and nuts. Bake in a greased 7 X 9 inch pan at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes. Quick, easy, delightful.

title: oyster pie
directions: Drain oysters, reserving 1/4 cup liquid; set aside.
Spread 1/3 of cracker crumbs in a buttered 3-quart casserole dish. Cover with oysters.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Top with rest of cracker crumbs and dot with butter
Combine reserved oyster liquid and half and half and pour over top of crumbs.
Bake in a 400° oven for a few minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Takes 50 to 55 minutes to cook.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: relish
directions: Pour boiling water over vegetables and let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Heat cider vinegar, salt, white sugar, celery salt, mustard seed and turmeric.
Pour over vegetables and boil 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain fat.
Combine beans and add sausage and onion in casserole dish.
In a small bowl combine the remaining ingredients.
Add to bean mixture.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be made ahead and reheated in crock-pot.

title: june's saucy sandwich rolls
directions: Brown wieners and onions in fat.
Take from heat; blend in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cook until center is tender, about 5 minutes.
Add cheese and heat until cheese melts; remove from heat.
Split buns and fill with mixture.
Wrap each in foil; heat in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Add ice to texture in blender until smooth.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs. Combine milk and lemon juice. Gradually add to creamed mixture. Reserve 1/2 cup flour.
Sift remaining flour with soda, salt and spices. Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix reserved flour with fruits and pecans.
Blend into dough.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: heavenly apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Stir in 1 cup cold water.
Chill until mixture is slightly thick.
Add apples, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Cover with dressing.

title: hot meatballs
directions: Mix all together, except for bottle of barbecue sauce.
Form into small meatballs.
Bake at 350° until starting to get brown. Place meatballs in crock-pot and add bottle of barbecue sauce. Cook on low until ready to serve.
Serve with cheese chunks and crackers.

title: saccharin pickles
directions: Mix ingredients (not cucumbers) but do not heat.
Pour this mixture over pickles and seal.
Store in a dark place.

title: hello dollies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and coconut in pan.
Dribble condensed milk over.
Sprinkle with walnut pieces.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatori
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken.
Brown slowly, turning once.
Remove chicken from pan.
Cook onions and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Combine remaining ingredients except for the wine.
Return chicken to skillet.
Pour tomato mixture over chicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in wine.
Cook uncovered, turning occasionally until fork tender.	Remove bay leaves. Skim off excess fat.
Serve with parmesan noodles.	Ladle sauce over noodles and chicken.

title: cream peach pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Add lemon juice and fruit.
Pour in two graham cracker crusts.
Garnish with peach slices or blueberries.

title: cheese and artichoke dip(great party dip)
directions: Drain artichokes; cut in small pieces or chop in food processor.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and Parmesan cheese in mixing bowl.
Add artichokes; stir in.
Place mixture in ovenproof dish.
Bake in 325° oven until heated through or microwave in microwave-safe dish
on High 2 or 3 minutes, turning to heat evenly.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: beans and chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Cook onion in shortening until tender in heavy skillet.
Cover and cook on low heat 30 minutes.
Add beans, applesauce and allspice.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, then add fruit. Sprinkle on top the brown sugar, nuts and coconut. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: glaze icing
directions: Mix and use as drizzle icing on any cake.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices and flour.
Add the slightly beaten eggs, milk and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Dust top with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes; reset oven to 350° and finish baking for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil in pan.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: spring relish
directions: Chop vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight; drain.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar and mix in celery and mustard seed.
Mix well and seal in airtight containers.

title: heavenly white cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Place bacon on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle wild rice over bacon.
Put chicken on top of rice and cover with soup plus 3/4 cup water.
Sprinkle seasoning mix over everything.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Enjoy.

title: coffee roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Put roast in pan and season.
Pour coffee into pan and cook for 20 minutes per pound of meat.
Take roast out of pan; cool and save drippings.
Add onion soup mix and thicken gravy.
Slice meat on the diagonal and place in gravy. Heat to warm.

title: delightful christmas scent
directions: Combine all ingredients in a tea kettle or saucepan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat, and simmer.
Check often and add additional water if needed.

title: old fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add margarine, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Coconut may be used, if desired.

title: basic pesto sauce
directions: Turn on the food processor fitted with the cutting blade. Drop the garlic cloves, one at a time into the work bowl with the blade running.
Allow the garlic to be finely chopped.
With the processor still running, slowly pour in the oil.
Add the pine nuts while the blade is running.
Turn off the processor and add the clean basil leaves which have been pulled from the woody stems. Replace the processor top and blend.
Salt and pepper and blend the whole mixture until smooth.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour until blended with fork (no lumps). Add melted butter, salt and egg yolks; beat with mixer until smooth.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Add milk slowly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in with whisk until blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes until brown at 350°. Check at 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dessert delicious
directions: Mix and pat down cookies and melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix instant pudding using only 2 cups of milk for both packages.
Then beat in 1 quart ice cream until blended.
Pour over cookie crust and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with 2 crushed Heath bars.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: diabetic applesauce cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients and combine with dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased and floured cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
(These cookies freeze well.)

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Wash blueberries and roll in 1/2 cup of flour.
Beat eggs well with fork and add to milk.
Add salt and baking powder to the remaining 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Stir into milk and egg mixture. Add melted oleo and fold in the well floured berries.
Generously grease double boiler.
Pour in mixture and cook until firm for about 2 hours.

title: pickled bologna brine
directions: Boil ingredients 1 minute.
Let cool and put in bologna.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/2 cup water for 5 minutes. Add a little Wesson oil and garlic salt.
Drain and set aside. Beat eggs well. Add cornbread mix; mix well.
Add broccoli, onion, salt, cottage cheese and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix well into soft batter.
Let rise about 1 1/2 hours.
Add 2 tablespoons melted oleo or oil.
Add enough self-rising flour until stiff.
Let rise and punch down.
Put in pans and let rise until doubled in size.
Brush top with oleo.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour then 300° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: In a large bowl with an electric mixer, beat together cake mix, oil, eggs, sour cream and cream of coconut.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown steak, peppers and onions.
Cover with water and simmer 1 hour.

title: carrot supreme
directions: Cook sliced carrots.
Mix soup, butter, vinegar and sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour over the carrots.
Slice pepper and onion and add to the carrots.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Warm and serve.

title: nelle's chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli till tender; drain.
Add lightly beaten eggs, mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper, soups, and 1 cup of cheese; mix well.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces; put into a casserole dish; then broccoli.
Spread soup mixture over broccoli and chicken.
Put 1/2 cup of cheese on top.
Top with croutons and potato sticks.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Drain carrots and cool.
Mix carrots, peppers and onions.
In a saucepan, mix soup, oil, sugar and vinegar.
Heat until sugar is melted.
Add mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Pour over carrots and let set overnight or 2 or 3 days.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done; drain.
Dice potatoes, pepper, onion and celery.
Combine all the dry ingredients, except eggs.
Add mayonnaise (or salad dressing).
Stir gently.
Add cut up eggs. Stir gently again.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: sheath cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
In saucepan combine Crisco, butter, cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Fold into first mixture while hot.
Pour into cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans; pour into pie shell.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Steam the broccoli, chopped onion, butter and water.
Set aside. Combine 1 cup light cream, eggs, salt, pepper, nutmeg and cheeses.
Add broccoli.
Line bottom of pie shell with tomato slices. Pour a layer of broccoli mixture.
Repeat with tomato slices until done.
Cover the top with bread crumbs. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Deep fry wings; put on towel to absorb oil.
Dip in sauce; put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to dry.
(Can add more sauce while baking.)

title: brisket in beer
directions: Season brisket with salt and pepper.
Place in a roasting pan. Pour beer around brisket and cover the pan tightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 325° for 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Remove meat and strain off grease from the pan.
Add enough water to the pan drippings to make a rich gravy.
Cut the meat into thin slices against the grain and serve with the gravy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cajun seasoned potatoes
directions: Mix the soup mix, oil and seasoned salt in a large plastic bag.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Place on baking sheet and bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: ham and collard soup
directions: Chop all the vegetables and slice the greens.
Combine the first 10 ingredients in a large soup pot; simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes, until all the vegetables are tender.
Add the beans, turkey ham, liquid smoke and lime juice; heat thoroughly.
Serve with pumpernickel bread spread with apple butter or applesauce. Serves 4.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Broth is good over cooked rice.

title: 30 day cake
directions: Mix peaches and 2
1/2 cups of sugar and stir every day for 10 days.
At the
end
of
10 days add pineapple and 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Mix and stir
for 10 more days.
At the end of 20 days add fruit cocktail
and
1/2 cups sugar.
Mix and stir for 10 more days.
Can be refrigerated after 30 days.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Cream sugars, margarine and peanut butter. Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt and add to mixture. Chill. Shape into balls; roll in sugar and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. While cookie is hot, press chocolate kiss in center of cookie.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 8 minutes. Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese; add sugar and spread over pretzels. Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water and pour over strawberries. Let stand 10 minutes to thaw berries. Pour over cream cheese. Let set in the refrigerator until set.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Combine apples and water in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until apples are soft and liquid evaporates.
Mash mixture with a fork.
Stir in butter, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; set apple mixture aside.

title: sausage pie
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Put rice in a bowl and cover with boiling water.
Set for 20 minutes.
Repeat 4 times.
Saute mushrooms, onions, celery and nuts in butter.
Combine with drained rice, milk and sherry.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: chop suey
directions: Cut the pork and chicken
in cubes.
Cut the cabbage, string beans, pepper and carrots in slices at least 2-inches long.
Cut snow peas in halves.
Saute the pork, chicken and lastly add the vegetables.
Pour chicken broth into vegetable mixture when vegetables are half cooked.
Prepare in a shallow dish cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar and salt; mix thoroughly until mixture comes to a thin sauce.
Pour the sauce into vegetables and mix lightly, being careful not to overcook greens. When sauce thickens, remove from fire.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix chopped suet, chopped raisins, chopped currants, citron, sweet milk, molasses, flour, salt and soda.
Add cinnamon, cloves, allspice and nutmeg to the flour before sifting.
Mix all together and cook in a mold or pan, covered.
Set in a kettle with water halfway up the side and cook 3 1/2 hours.

title: lemony cream cheese pound cake
directions: In large bowl, beat white sugar, butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in lemon juice, vanilla, lemon and orange extracts, nutmeg and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 12 cup tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack 10 minutes.

title: basic marinata sauce(to be used alone over pasta)
directions: In a large skillet saute onions in olive oil.
When almost light golden, add garlic.
Continue to saute 2 additional minutes. Add 2 cans tomatoes and add basil, oregano, parsley, 1 teaspoon each (more if desired) salt, black pepper plus red wine and red pepper, if desired.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over favorite pasta.

title: 24 hour omelet
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Butter one side.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Place buttered side up in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Beat together milk, eggs, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Add meat.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovering the last 10 minutes.

title: ole-time pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Alternate with sour cream; begin and end with flour.
Stir in mace and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, until separated from sides of pan.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake according to directions and let cool.
Prepare the vanilla pudding.
When cake is cold, crumble 1/2 of cake in bottom of the bowl.
Add 1/2 of the pineapple (do not drain).
Layer with 1/2 of the pudding and top with 1 carton Cool Whip.
Repeat with remaining cake, pineapple, pudding and Cool Whip.
Top with shredded coconut and pecan pieces.

title: oregon beans
directions: Brown beef, sausage ring and onion together and drain well. Pour beans and juice in with meat.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and salt and pepper
Simmer all together.
Serve with corn bread.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows over slow heat.
Butter tube pan. Coat popcorn real good with above.
Toss in M&M's.
Press into tube pan firm, not hard.
When real cool, turn out of pan.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Mix jello and allow it to set.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2 pan.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, drain; crush chips and put in a 9 X 13 pan. Mix nacho cheese, cream of mushroom and Rotel into hamburger mixture.
Stir; bring to a boil.
Then, pour on top of nacho chips.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients (butter, flour and brown sugar) together and set aside for the topping. Mix together by spoon the sugar, egg, milk and butter; stir in the flour and baking powder. Add raspberries.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full and sprinkle topping mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: very cheesy macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni per directions until al dente or still slightly firm.
Drain well. In another saucepan, 3/4 full of water, bring to boil; add broccoli.
Reduce heat to medium until al dente. Drain.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
In medium saucepan, melt butter; add flour, stirring, 1 minute, until smooth.
Gradually whisk in milk, stirring continually, until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; reserve 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Stir remaining Cheddar, Gruyere, Parmesan, salt and cayenne into sauce.
Add broccoli and macaroni to sauce.
Pour into dish; bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle reserved cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: fey's all spice custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake
mix as directed on box. Stir in apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: persian meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl with your fingers.
Pack into buttered pottery loaf pan, bake at 350° for about one hour (or more if you like it nice and brown).

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Prepare first 3 flavors of Jell-O separately using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water each.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) square pans and chill until set.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off excess fat/grease. Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add more ketchup, if needed.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use four teaspoonfuls of mix to a coffee mug.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring the last 5 ingredients to a boil; pour this mixture over carrots, onion and bell pepper.
Refrigerate.

title: jam cake
directions: Soak raisins at least 2 hours in crushed pineapple with juice. Butter 2 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Line cake pans with waxed paper.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: speedy sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in hot skillet until brown; add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender (about 5 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Serve over hamburger buns.
Serves 6.

title: no-salt seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small jar with a shaker top.
Use in cooking foods or place it on the table to be used in place of salt.

title: chicken in a garden
directions: Layer vegetables in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Add chicken.
Mix all other ingredients (except onions) and pour over chicken and veggies.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Add onions on top.
Bake additional 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
If using a 9 x 13-inch metal pan, bake at 350°.
If using a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, bake at 325°.

title: chocolate lush(use 9 x 13 inch pan)
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2 1/2-quart covered casserole dish.
In casserole dish, layer potatoes, then sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper on each layer.
Dot each layer with butter. Omit the flour from the top layer and pour milk over all.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake until done for another 30 minutes.

title: mashed peas and potatoes
directions: Peel and boil the potatoes and onion.
Drain.
Mash with chicken broth and butter.
Add salt and spices. Stir in hot peas. Microwave 3 minutes or until hot. Serve hot.

title: mom's drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla together. Add buttermilk. Stir until mixed. Add dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet, slightly floured. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. (Sugar may be sprinkled on top before baking.)

title: sauteed spinach a la catalain
directions: Wash spinach well.
Pat dry and set aside. Toast pine nuts in a 350° oven for about 1 to 2 minutes. Turn frequently.
Set aside.

title: reuben sandwich casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased well) crumble corned beef in bottom.
Put sauerkraut over corned beef.
Put tomatoes over sauerkraut.
Over tomatoes, drizzle Thousand Island dressing. Spread Cheddar cheese over dressing.
Crumble or cube rye bread over top of cheese to cover.
Bake at 375° until it bubbles, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot banana glory(simple, low-fat snack)
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Wrap unpeeled banana in aluminum foil and bake 30 minutes. Carefully unwrap and peel banana.
Transfer to serving plate. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Top with whipped topping.
Makes 1 serving.
Contains per serving 110 calories, 1 g. protein, 1 g. fat, 27 g. carbohydrate, 10 mg. calcium, 1 mg. sodium and 0 mg. cholesterol.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Beat zucchini, baking soda, sugar and shortening.
Add egg and dry ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: biscuits or quick rolls
directions: Cut flour, sugar and shortening until crumbly.
Add yeast and milk; mix as for biscuits, using more flour if necessary.
Roll out to 1-inch thickness and cut.
Place on greased pan and let sit 30 to 60 minutes.
Bake in 400° oven until browned.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out and cut with small cutter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: french bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, butter and 2 cups flour.
Beat with a spoon until thoroughly mixed.
Gradually add remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Knead on a lightly floured surface for 5 to 10 minutes or until dough is elastic and not sticky.
Place in a greased bowl; cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and place on lightly floured surface.
Divide into 2 pieces.
Shape each piece into a long narrow loaf about 14 inches long.
Lightly grease inside of Ekco French bread pan; sprinkle 1 teaspoon cornmeal in each section.
Shake pan to distribute evenly.
Place loaves in pan.
Make sure the loaves do not come any closer than 1 1/2 inches to end of pan.
With a sharp knife, make 3 or 4 diagonal 1/4-inch deep slashes on the top of each loaf.
Do not cover.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size, about 45 minutes.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan at once.

title: beef brisket #2
directions: Put meat in heavy foil, fat side up.
Put mixture of remaining ingredients on meat.
Seal tightly.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour per pound.

title: low-fat turkey meatballs(23% calories from fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place meatballs in spray-coated pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until no longer pink; remove from pan.
Use as directed in Minestrone Meat Soup and Spaghetti and Turkey Meatballs.
Makes 6 dozen mini meatballs.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini and scrub lightly to remove any grit or wax. Parboil for 10 minutes; drain, cool and split lengthwise.
Remove pulp and chop it finely.
Saute garlic in oil until golden brown. Discard garlic and saute mushrooms in the oil with the onions. Add herbs, pepper and zucchini pulp.
Cool.
Mix in the slightly beaten egg and fill the cavity of each zucchini half with the mixture.
Place stuffed zucchini in an oiled shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in pan.
Cook until brown (about the color of Heath bar filling), about 10 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Pour into buttered round cake pan.

title: potato rolls
directions: Mash potatoes; add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Cream well.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add to lukewarm milk.
Add to potato mixture.
Add sifted flour to make dough stiff.
Pour on floured board.
Knead well.
Put in a bowl and will double in bulk overnight.
Take out what you need.
Roll out.
Grease with butter. Leave remainder in refrigerator.
(Will keep a long time.)
You can just use what is needed.
Bake at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add butter beans, peas, corn, potatoes, green beans and carrots.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add tomatoes, mustard, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium-low to desired thickness.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium sized bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased brownie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool, then cut into squares and top with Cool Whip or whipped cream, if desired.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Heat pecans, brown sugar and margarine in sauce pan until brown and crunchy.
Put aside to cool.
Mix sweetened condensed milk, vanilla flavoring, maple flavoring, sugar and enough milk to finish filling freezer.
Cool in refrigerator until ready to freeze.
Add pecan mixture just before freezing.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and green pepper.
Mix macaroni, ground chuck, onion, green pepper, cheese and ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: franks and corn fritters
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, chili powder (optional) and seasoned salt.
Combine the egg, milk and melted Crisco.
Add to dry ingredients with the drained corn and chopped frankfurters.
Stir just until moistened.
Drop batter by tablespoons into heated shortening, a few at a time, until golden brown (about 3 to 4 minutes), turning once.
Drain on paper toweling.
Serve with catsup and mustard.
Makes about 24 fritters.

title: savory crust chicken bake
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine butter, sour cream and egg. Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and thyme, blending at low speed until thoroughly mixed.
In ungreased pie pan or baking dish, spread batter evenly over bottom and up sides of 1-inch of rim.

title: splendid strawberry and spinach salad
directions: Make dressing:
Combine olive oil, orange juice, vinegar, honey, poppy seed and mustard.
Combine spinach, strawberries, yellow pepper rings and pecans.
Toss well with dressing.
Garnish with edible flowers or cantaloupe on the side.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and margarine.
Boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Then beat for a few minutes (3 to 5 minutes). Pour into greased pan.
Cut when cool in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Makes 5 1/2 pounds.

title: french onion soup
directions: Thinly slice French bread.
Brush the slices of bread with olive oil and garlic; put in a 350° oven to dry out, don't burn. Slice and coarsely chop onions.
Saute in oil and butter until brown.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and flour when beginning to saute. Add stock and wine and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Break up dried bread into chunks.
Put in bottom of soup tureen.
Alternate layers of bread and cheese.
Pour stock over top and add cognac. Put in oven to melt cheese.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Beat first 5 ingredients in medium bowl to blend.
Arrange chilies from 1 can in prepared dish, covering bottom completely.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of each cheese.
Repeat, layering twice.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together the margarine, oil and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Roll 1 teaspoon of dough into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Press down on greased cookie sheet with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: low-fat chicken or fish batter
directions: Mix Pet milk and egg in a bowl.
Wash chicken or skin it.
Dip chicken into bowl of mix.
Shake salt, pepper and garlic on chicken.
Roll into flour and shake off excess flour.
Use glass dish or saucepan; bake at 450° about 25 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and dry.
Mix together other ingredients, except margarine.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Place pieces of chicken with skin down in melted margarine. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: syrup cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Add dry ingredients all together.
Add buttermilk last.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: enchiladas with swiss cheese and kale
directions: Lay out tortillas; sprinkle each with 1/4 of kale, scallions and cheese.
Roll up each tortilla and press in filling with back of spoon.
Pour oil into preheated cast-iron skillet or into nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
When oil is hot, place enchiladas seam side down in skillet.
Pour tomato sauce over enchiladas and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 5 minutes, basting frequently.
Place enchiladas on serving platter and square off insides with spatula.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Place 1 layer of green beans, corn and peas in glass casserole.
Dilute soup with milk; stir in salt.
Pour over vegetables, cover and bake at 305° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Add the cream cheese to bowl and let sit to soften.
Add whole package of Italian seasoning mix and mayonnaise.
Mix together. Spread on bread (not too thinly).
Place cucumber slice on top. Sprinkle with dill weed on top of cucumber slice.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough 1/8-inch thick with a knife and overlap on a 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; mix until creamy.
Spread onto cooled cookie dough.
Arrange fruit and spread with marmalade.
Chill. Assorted fruits may include:
bananas, grapes, kiwi, strawberries, peaches and apples.

title: pinto bean tamales
directions: Boil husks in hot water to soften; drain and pat dry. Mix beans and cornmeal. For each tamale, lay 3 overlapping corn husks on a flat surface. Spread 1/3 cup bean mixture on center husk; spoon about a tablespoon of beef down the center of beans. Lift sides of other 2 corn husks to wrap beans around beef; then wrap corn husks around to enclose beans and beef. Tie ends securely with string. In a large skillet, combine tomato paste, chili powder, salt and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil. Place a single layer of tamales in sauce; cover and simmer 30 minutes. Lift out cooked tamales and repeat with remainder, adding water if needed. Makes 1 dozen tamales.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Combine the eggs, bread crumbs, tomato juice, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix with beef, divide beef mixture in half.
On wax paper, pat each half into a 12 x 10-inch rectangular pan.
Arrange ham slices on top, leaving small margin like jelly roll, sealing edges.
Place, seam side down, on 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Place cheese slices on top, return to oven until cheese melts.
Makes 2 loaves. Or microwave 12 to 15 minutes in 2 quart baking dish, turning 1/4 turn every 3 minutes.

title: batter-fried fish
directions: Wash fillets and place in
flat baking dish.
Cover with buttermilk and lemon slices.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Cut each fillet in half to resemble a triangle.
Coat each piece with pancake mix.
In a separate bowl, combine 2 cups pancake mix with club soda to resemble consistency of buttermilk.
Coat fillets and deep fry for about 4 minutes. Keep warm in a 300° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit cobbler(microwave recipe)
directions: Mix together berries or fruit, water, Jell-O and sugar.

Place into a 2-quart casserole, cover and place in microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes. In a small bowl, stir together biscuit mix, the 1/4 cup sugar, nutmeg, milk and vanilla. Stir only enough to blend.

Using a tablespoon, drop 8 dumplings on top of Jell-O mixture in a circle around the edge of the dish. Place uncovered dish in microwave oven and cook for 5 to 7 minutes, giving dish 1/4 turn every 2 minutes until dumplings are no longer doughy.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Pound chicken breasts thin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Chop the onions and parsley; have all other ingredients ready. Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat 2 minutes each side. Transfer to a warm serving platter.
Add green onion, lemon juice, brandy, mustard and parsley.
Cook 15 seconds, whisking.
Whisk in chicken broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve.

title: divinity peanut butter roll
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to hard boil stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to syrup mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat 4 to 5 minutes.
Knead on board covered with powdered sugar.
Roll in oblong shape.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up; chill, then cut.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 4 minutes.
Lightly spray bread pans with Pam.
Pour in batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove bread and cool on a rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: porchetta (roast pork)
directions: Spread porchetta flat lengthwise and make slits in meat, from top to bottom, all the way across the roast, about one inch apart, being careful not to cut through the meat.
Scatter garlic and finocchio over meat.
Add salt and pepper.

title: puppy chow
directions: Put Chex cereal in a flat cake pan.
Set aside.
Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter in microwave or on stove top. Add vanilla after it has melted.
Pour melted mixture over cereal and stir easily until evenly coated.
Transfer coated cereal to a large bowl with lid for shaking.
Pour powdered sugar over cereal. Shake until evenly coated.

title: not so sloppy joes
directions: Heat oil.
Stir in onion, celery, green pepper and oregano. Cook until tender.
Crumble in the ground beef.
Cook thoroughly. Stir in remaining ingredients through the black pepper.
Cook longer.
Stir again and add Tabasco, if using, and cook until bubbly and heated through.
Spoon over toasted rolls (poppy seed) and serve.

title: pork chops and potatoes in skillet
directions: Trim fat from chops; brown chops in skillet for 10 minutes on each side.
Remove chops from skillet.
Deglaze pan with 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add mushroom soup; stir.
Add chopped onion.
Add sliced potatoes; stir.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover; simmer for approximately 45 minutes, until potatoes are done.
(Stir occasionally, adding water as necessary.
Leave chops on top.) Serve.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.

title: chocolate kraut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan. Drain, rinse and chop kraut.
In a large mixing bowl, sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, salt and cocoa; mix well. Alternately add flour mixture and water. Add kraut and mix well.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes. Spread cherry pie filling over top after cool.

title: pecan pizza
directions: Roll out dough and place in a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Be sure to seal all perforations well.
Cook at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: sunshine macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, Velveeta cheese, celery, ham, pimento and green pepper.
Add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Mix well. Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: upside-down meat loaf
directions: Combine and mix thoroughly.
Press into pan over catsup and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
After baked, turn out upside down onto platter.
Slice and serve.

title: one-dish meal
directions: Combine beans, basil and salt.
Pile in center of 10-inch pie plate.
Combine macaroni and cheese, mustard and Worcestershire sauce; surround beans with mixture.
Place sausages, spoke fashion, on macaroni.
Brush beans and sausages with butter. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: sweet pickled beets
directions: Cut beet tops off, leaving 1-inch stem.
Leave on roots.
Wash beets.
Cover with water and boil until tender (like a potato). Pour out juice through strainer, saving 3 to 4 cups.
Rinse beets with cold water.
Clean skins and bottoms off.
Cut into pieces, preparing remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Add beets and boil 1/2 hour.
Jar and seal.
Makes 12 pints.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out the 2 pie crusts together. Spread the apples onto the crust and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up like a jelly roll and slice into 1/4 to 1/2 inch slices.
Place in baking pan.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, then fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix ingredients in small bowl.
Cook on High in microwave for 4 minutes.
Beat well.
Pour into pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch square Pyrex dish.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 2 or 3 layers.
Cool.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Beat vigorously about 20 strokes.
Allow dough to rest (about 5 minutes).
Heat oven to 425°.
Divide dough in half.
On lightly greased baking sheets, pat each half into circle with floured fingers. Spread with pizza sauce. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Add toppings. Bake 20 to 25
minutes.
Makes 2 (10-inch) pizzas.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in mixer bowl at medium speed. Spread in bottom of 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Spread pecans on top of mixture.
Mix last 4 ingredients well and gently pour over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until firm to touch in center.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and continue beating.
Add flour alternate with vanilla and lemon extract and 7-Up.
Bake in large tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
If desired, Seven Minute Icing may be used.

title: nugget pecan pie
directions: Mix together syrup and sugar.
Add melted butter, then mix in eggs and vanilla.
Let stand a short time.
Place pecan pieces in bottom of unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Pour filling over the nuts and cover with the pecan halves.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Place in a baking dish in order given and bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: creamy corn soup
directions: Combine flour and butter to make roux.
Cook in 3-quart pot until lightly browned.
Add onion and saute for 3 to 4 minutes. Then add rest of ingredients and bring to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: russian tea
directions: Soybeans are known to be one of the higher quality vegetable protein sources. When eaten in combination with the protein found in grains, dairy products or nuts and seeds, the quality of the soy protein is about equal to that of meat with less than 1% fat and no cholesterol.

title: southwest chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil; remove from skillet.
Cook peppers and onion until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chicken. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring to boil pepper, salt, sugar, oil and red wine vinegar. Drain all liquid from cans.
In bowl, mix all vegetables.
Pour boiled liquid over vegetables and marinate overnight.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix ingredients until crumbly and press half of mixture into greased pan.
Add berry filling mixed as for pie and then press remaining half of crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bay hill club's blt soup
directions: Saute bacon until brown.
Remove bacon and saute onion and romaine lettuce in bacon drippings for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour off excess drippings.
Add tomatoes, chicken stock, bay leaf, browned bacon and garlic.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for one hour.

title: oven buttered corn sticks
directions: Melt oleo in oblong pan.
Combine biscuit mix and corn.
Stir until dough is formed.
Knead about 15 strokes on lightly floured surface.
Roll to 6 x 10-inch rectangle, then cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
Roll in melted oleo in pan and arrange in single layer. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, cream of tartar and boiling water.
Boil to 246° or until mixture forms a firm ball when dropped in cold water.
Add walnuts and cool.
Turn out onto waxed paper to cool. Separate the nuts.
Pecans may also be used.

title: unleavened bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Knead it.
Shape into square or round loaf.
You can score it, put lines in it, for breaking. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: farm country eggs(microwave recipe)
directions: Place bacon on rack; cover with paper towel and cook for 4 minutes at 100% power or until done.
Cool, crumble and set aside. Place butter, potatoes and vegetables in an 8-inch round microwave-safe dish, such as a cake plate.
Cook uncovered for 6 minutes at 100% power, stirring once.
While vegetables are cooking, mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Flatten potato mixture and pour the eggs over the top.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave at 70% power for 5 to 7 minutes or until the eggs are almost set.
Stir once.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese over top. Heat, uncovered, for additional 1 minute, until cheese starts to melt.
Remove and let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Divide all ingredients except tomatoes in half; layer in well-greased 3-quart rectangular casserole pan.
Begin with chicken sprinkled lightly with chili powder and garlic salt. Follow with 1/2 soup mixture, tortillas, onion, pepper, cheese and chicken broth.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Cook broccoli according to directions. Drain.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk according to directions. Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding in large bowl.
Let set overnight.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine cake mix with 1/3 cup evaporated milk and margarine. Add pecans. Press half of the mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Drop chocolate chips evenly
over hot cake. Then spread melted caramels over chocolate chips.
Crumble remaining cake mixture on top.
Return to oven and continue baking an additional 15 to 18 minutes.

title: lemon coffeecake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Add butter, buttermilk and lemon rind; beat until smooth. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold in.
Turn into a 10-inch greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, until a cake tester inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 15 minutes; remove from pan. In small bowl, combine confectioners sugar and lemon juice; stir until smooth.
When cake is completely cool, drizzle with lemon glaze and garnish as desired.

title: air force one salad
directions: Break up noodles into small pieces (discard flavor pack). Brown noodles, sesame seeds and almonds in butter. Let cool.

title: spicy scallop potatoes
directions: Substitute
half
of
the
liquid
called for with mild picante sauce, then follow the rest of the instructions on the box.
Men love it; women too.

title: lemon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add pecans if desired.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Remove from oven; drizzle with Clear Lemon Glaze.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely. Store wrapped.
Makes one 9 x 5-inch loaf.

title: linguine and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil over medium heat.
Add tomatoes, basil, sugar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in cream and butter.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Toss with cooked linguine.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: sparkling dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ginger ale.
Chill until thickened.
Add fruit and pour into individual dishes and chill until set.
Serves 6.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a buttered casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with 1 1/2 cups crushed cornflakes. Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.

title: spanish indian baked corn
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Add onion, celery, and bell pepper; saute 2 minutes over low heat. Set aside.
In medium pan, melt 1/4 pound butter; add milk, corn, jalapenos, pimentos, salt, and sugar; heat over low heat.
Add bacon-vegetable mixture and 1 cup corn bread crumbs to corn mixture.
Heat well, stirring frequently.
Transfer to an 8 inch square by 1 1/2 inch pan.
Moisten remaining corn bread crumbs with remaining butter and sprinkle on top of corn mixture. Bake at 350° until crumbs are light brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy chocolate delight
directions: Heat all but 3 squares of chocolate with 1/4 cup of milk in double boiler.
Stir until completely melted.
Beat in other ingredients; pour in pie shell.
Shave chocolate on top and refrigerate.

title: quickie pork chop casserole
directions: Trim all fat from pork chops. Cut them in thin strips. Mix all ingredients together except the crackers and butter. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 1 hour in a preheated 375° F oven. Crush crackers, pour melted butter over them. Remove casserole from the oven and top with cracker crumbs. Return to oven until cracker crumbs are browned.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 8 ingredients in order given in bowl or 13 x 9 casserole dish.

title: meal in a pumpkin
directions: Cook ground beef and onion.
Drain excess grease.
Add mushrooms, water chestnuts and soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Clean seed and excess pulp out of pumpkin.
Draw face with a magic marker.
Put all ingredients inside pumpkin and cook for 1 hour or until pumpkin is tender inside (oven set at 350°).
Double recipe if desired.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiled water.
Add 2 cups ice cream and stir until well dissolved and mixed.
Add the thawed strawberries and syrup.
Pour into favorite mold.
Let set.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana-date-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs. Mix well.
Stir in bananas.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well. Stir in nuts and dates.
Pour into greased, wax paper-lined 9 5/8 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch pan and let stand for 15 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes. Turn out on rack to finish cooling.

title: skillet chicken couscous
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Arrange chicken cubes in a single layer.
Brown chicken over moderate heat, turning to brown evenly.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover tightly and turn heat to low.
Simmer 3 or 4 minutes until most of the liquid is absorbed by the couscous.
Remove from heat and keep tightly covered until served.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lela callis thompson's vegetable casserole
directions: Combine in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs dotted with margarine.
Bake at 350°, covered, for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma miller's noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon oil until onion is transparent.
Brown ground chuck, then add the tomatoes.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes, then add soup and milk.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Butter large (3-quart) casserole.
Put cooked noodles in ground chuck sauce; mix well, then put in casserole.
Cut cheese in strips; push in noodles and sauce.
More cheese, the better! Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana and cheese pie
directions: Brown pie shell to lightly brown.
Remove from oven.
Puree 3 bananas and place in mixing bowl with Ricotta cheese, cream cheese, eggs, light cream, ground cinnamon, ginger and honey.
Mix and blend well.
Slice 3 bananas into thin rounds and place slices into pie crust.
Pour banana and cheese filling over sliced bananas.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes or until browned.
Shut oven off; leave pie in oven with door open for 5 to 10 minutes to settle.
Serve warm or chilled with whipped cream topping.

title: fruitcake bars
directions: Chop pineapple and cherries.
Spread pecans evenly over bottom of greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Spoon batter over pecan halves, pressing evenly with dampened hands.
Sprinkle fruit over batter and press in slightly.
Bake in a 300° to 325° oven for one hour.
(Keep a check.)
Cool in pan.
When cold, cut into bars.
Makes 32 to 36 bars.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Add sour cream, soup and cheese.
Add thawed potatoes and onion.
Bake for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients until well folded. Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut broccoli into flowerets and stems. Peel and slice stems in 1/4-inch rounds. Wash spinach thoroughly and tear.
Saute onion in oil.
Add broccoli, green pepper and carrot.
Then add basil and bay leaf.
Stir well and add tomatoes. Bring to a boil.
Cover. Turn heat to low and simmer for 15 minutes or until veggies are just tender. Stir in spinach. Drain off excess liquid and put veggies into a 13 x 9-inch oval baking dish.
Spread potatoes over top and bake for 10 to 15 minutes until potato is hot. Shake paprika over top.
Serves 4 to 6. Potatoes can be put in pastry bag.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour in a greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan and pour out.
Preheat oven before cooking.

title: old fashion salmon patties
directions: Remove bones and dark skin from canned salmon.
Add eggs and mash well.
Add flour until thick and sticky.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place corn oil in thick skillet.
Place salmon mixture a tablespoon at a time in grease before it gets hot.
Turn often as each patty will rise twice original size.
After grease gets hot, reduce heat to medium to prevent burning.
Serve with hot buttered biscuits and syrup.
May also serve with catsup or tartar sauce.

title: crock-pot dinner
directions: In crock-pot mix together soups and water. Slice potatoes and put in soup.
Rinse off dried beef; cut into bite size pieces. Add to soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.Cook on low heat about 8 to 9 hours.
Also good with ham.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: If using jelly, spread it on crust.
Mix all the other ingredients together in bowl.
Spread over jelly and refrigerate to set.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar and canned milk 5 minutes, slow.
Be sure it boils for 5 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips, candy bars, marshmallow, syrup and nuts.
Grease cookie sheet and spread the mixture on it. Be sure to break the candy bars in small pieces.
Makes 4 pounds.

title: chocolate oatmeal candies
directions: Place sugar, syrup, milk, butter, salt, cocoa and peanut butter in heavy saucepan over medium-high heat.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Boil until a drop in cool water forms a soft ball. Remove from heat.
Stir in oatmeal, vanilla, coconut and chopped nuts (if desired).
Beat until thick and mixture begins to lose its shine.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream sugars and margarine at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg whites and vanilla; beat well. Combine crumbs and next 4 ingredients.
Stir well.
With mixer running at low speed, add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with crumb mixture.
Spoon batter into a 9-inch square baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan on wire rack. Yields 12 servings.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except wieners, in mixing bowl.
Roll or dip wieners in mixture, coating well.
Place in preheated deep fryer.
Remove when brown.

title: london broil
directions: Peel garlic and cut in half.
Rub both sides of flank steak with garlic.
Brush with French dressing or marinate steak in dressing a few hours.
Preheat broiler.
Place meat on rack 1 1/2 to 2 inches from heat.
Broil about 5 minutes or until meat is browned.
Season with salt and pepper.
Turn steak and broil about 5 minutes longer.
Do not overcook.
Season again with salt and pepper.
Place steak on heated platter.
Cut in very thin slices diagonally across grain.
Serve at once.

title: onion soup meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Mold into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Top loaf with catsup if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove promptly from oven to keep moist taste.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired, or glaze with water and confectioners sugar mixture.

title: cheddar cheese broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in pan; add onion, carrots and celery and saute over low heat until soft.
Add flour and cornstarch and cook until bubbly.
Add broth and milk slowly; stir until smooth.
Add soda and grated cheese.
Season to taste.
Add cooked broccoli and heat through.
Add parsley just before serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift all-purpose flour, soda and salt together. Cream margarine, shortening, sugar and vanilla flavoring together. Mix thoroughly. Add egg. Cream until mixture is fluffy. Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth. Blend in 2 tablespoons milk. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of water glass which has been dipped in sugar (may have to wet bottom of glass). Bake at 400° about 12 minutes or until done.

title: orange slice cookies or candy
directions: Finely chop orange slices.
Mix all ingredients, except powdered sugar, together.
Bake on slightly greased cookie sheet at 275° for about 30 minutes or until it looks done.
Do not let it brown or it will be too hard.
Just let candy kindly melt.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put in saucepan, except strawberries, and boil until clear and a little thick.
Let cool and pour over sliced berries.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix well.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Mix and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Use 2-quart glass mixing bowl safe for microwave.
Mix peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir; cook 4 minutes.
Quickly stir in oleo and extract.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add soda; stir fast.
Mixture will foam.
Pour out quickly on cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Cool 15 minutes.
Break up into pieces.
Store in tight can or jar.

title: pistachio nut salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple; leave the juice in.
Add marshmallows and nuts (chopped).
Mix in Cool Whip into all of it.

title: cookie cutter cookies(this makes 1 really tasty cookie)
directions: You mix all ingredients together and stir it.
Then you take it out and you pound it and roll it and press your cookie cutter in the dough.
Put the cookie on a tray.
Then you put some grease on it before it goes in the oven.
You make it shine with the grease. Then you put some sprinkles on top of it.
Put it in the oven. Bake at 300° for 50 hours.
Then you take it out and you can eat it.
